title: parmesan chicken
directions: Dip chicken in Viva and seasoning mixture.
Mix parsley, Parmesan and bread crumbs together.
Dip chicken in dry mixture. Spray pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: alma's 7-up cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Fold in the 7-Up. Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fried potatoes (hillbilly style)
directions: Peel and sliced potatoes. Pour oil into cast-iron skillet. Add potatoes to oil. Add salt, pepper and sugar. Crack the lid and heat on high until potatoes begin to sizzle. Turn heat down to medium and fry, turning every 5 minutes until brown and tender.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook pared squash and onion in enough water to cover for 8 to 15 minutes.
When tender, drain and mash.
Add other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Bake in long, buttered casserole for 1 hour at 300°.
Serves 8.

title: bacon cheeseburgers
directions: Mix ground beef with remaining ingredients.
Shape into patties.
Grill until done.

title: mom's persimmon cookies
directions: Blend in order given.
Bake on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: cream puff ring
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and butter to boiling in a 1-quart saucepan.
Stir in flour.
Stir vigorously until mixture forms a ball, about 1 minute.
Add eggs; beat until smooth.
Drop dough by tablespoons onto greased baking sheet to form an 8-inch ring.
(See Note.)
Smooth ring lightly with spatula.
Bake until puffed and golden, 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool ring.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick melted butter with graham cracker crumbs; pat evenly in pan (9 x 13-inch or two 8-inch square).
Beat together with electric mixer for no less than 15 minutes the remaining butter, sugar and eggs; spread over crumbs.
Cover with sliced bananas, spread with drained pineapple, cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours or overnight.

title: chinese new year cookies
directions: Melt chips in microwave.
Add noodles and peanuts.
Drop from spoon on wax paper or tray.
Let cool.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix all together until creamy.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Line a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with graham crackers, then add 1/2 of mixture.
Then put another layer graham crackers over top, then last 1/2 mixture and another layer of graham crackers.
Then take a container of milk chocolate frosting and spread over top.

title: nut-date-crumb cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and margarine as for pie.
Take out 1 cup.

title: cream cheese mashed potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients; put in 2-quart casserole dish and dot with butter.
Sprinkle paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate amaretto frosting
directions: Heat cream and butter in a medium saucepan over medium-high heat, stirring until butter melts and cream just comes to a boil. Remove from heat; add chocolate chips and stir until completely melted.
Stir in Amaretto.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours, stirring every 1/2 hour or so as mixture cools and thickens.
Frost cake and refrigerate.
Frosting gets quite soft at room temperature.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring to a boil (until makes a bubble in glass of water).
Add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop on wax paper.

title: citrus pepper roast beef
directions: Combine spices and rub evenly over surface of rib roast.
Do not add water.
Do not cover roast.
Roast at 350° for 3 to 4 hours, depending on whether you like your meat rare, medium or well done.
Let stand 20 minutes before carving.

title: feather potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a buttered casserole at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Squeeze potatoes to get off as much water as possible. Combine potatoes, eggs, onion, flour, sugar, salt and pepper. Beat well.
Drop mixture by heaping tablespoons on well greased hot griddle or pan and spread thinly.
Fry both sides until a golden brown.
Add more shortening to continue frying as needed.

title: "the best" baked beans
directions: Brown one pound of ground beef; drain. Rinse with hot water. Drain again. Fry 1/2 pound bacon and use drippings to saute the onions until tender.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Top each piece of chicken with Swiss cheese.
Mix together soup, milk and wine.
Pour over chicken.
Top with croutons.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes in casserole dish.
Serves 4.

title: apple casserole
directions: Peel and core apples, then layer in a casserole dish.
Melt margarine and pour all over apples.
Mix the sugars, cinnamon, nutmeg and flour, then sprinkle over top.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry nut salad
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups of boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce and stir to dissolve.
Add diced apples and nuts.
Chill until set.
Will keep for several days.

title: peach french toast
directions: In sauce pan, bring brown sugar and water to boil; simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour into greased 13x9 baking dish.
Top with peaches.
Arrange bread over peaches.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix well and cover ingredients.
Store in refrigerator. Knead once a day for three days. On the forth day make 3 rolls 2 1/2 x 6 inches. Bake at 150° for 10 hours on broiler pan or oven racks.

title: greek country salad
directions: Prepare Oil and Vinegar Dressing.
Tear curly endive and romaine lettuce into bite-size pieces.
Place on a large salad bowl.
Add cucumber, tomatoes, olives and onions.
Pour Oil and Vinegar Dressing over salad.
Toss lightly.
Top with cheese. Makes 6 servings.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Cook eggs and remove shells.
In a 1/2-gallon container, put pickled beets, eggs and cloves.
Fill the rest of the jar with a mixture of 1/2 water and 1/2 vinegar.
Stir.
Leave out for 30 minutes and refrigerate.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine ingredients and put into casserole. Top with cheese and potato chips. Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Spoon half of batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cake will not test done.
Cool cake 10 minutes.

title: barbecue burgers
directions: Combine meat, celery, parsley, herbs and seasonings.
Add 1/4 cup barbecue sauce.
Mix; shape into 6 patties.
Grill patties until done as desired.
Split and toast muffins; butter them lightly.
Cut tomato in 6 slices.
Place 1 slice on each muffin half.
Top with hot burger patty.
Add spoonful of barbecue sauce. Serve at once.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch casserole dish. Combine all ingredients except cornmeal.
Stir in cornmeal mix just until blended.
Pour into prepared pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lizzie's fruit cake cookies
directions: Cut fruit into small pieces. Combine fruit and nuts. Dredge in 1 cup of flour and set aside. Cream margarine and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add pineapple juice, milk and dry ingredients. Mix well. Add fruit and nuts. Work well with hands so fruit is well mixed. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 275° for 12 to 15 minutes. Yields
24 dozen.

title: mexican brownies
directions: Put cheese in dish. Whisk eggs and cream. Spread bacon, then peppers. Pour eggs and whipped cream over. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. If the dish doesn't jiggle, it's done!

title: american lasagna
directions: In a skillet over medium heat, brown ground beef, onion and garlic; drain fat.
Mix in basil, oregano, brown sugar, 1-1/2 tsp. salt, diced tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil.
Add lasagna noodles, and cook for 5 to 8 minutes, or until al dente; drain.
Lay noodles flat on towels, and blot dry.
In a medium bowl, mix together eggs, ricotta, Parmesan cheese, parsley and 1 teaspoon salt.
Layer 1/3 of the lasagna noodles in the bottom of a 9 x 13 inch baking dish. Cover noodles with 1/2 ricotta mixture, 1/2 of the mozzarella cheese and 1/3 of the sauce.
Repeat.
Top with remaining noodles and sauce.
Sprinkle additional Parmesan cheese over the top.
Bake in the preheated oven 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken until tender. Cool, bone and slice. Save broth. Melt butter.
Add flour and cook until smooth. Add broth, milk, cornstarch and cheese.
Cook over low heat until sauce is smooth. Cook broccoli until tender.
Place layer of broccoli in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with florets turned out. Top with chicken, batter and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Bake at 350° until slightly browned.

title: whiskey slush
directions: Mix and freeze 24 hours.
Serve with 7-Up.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix all together.
This will make 2 large layers.
Bake at 350° until cake springs back.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add butter, vanilla, vinegar and water. Mix together and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cook cake according to package directions. Make 2 layers and split, making 4 layers. Mix sour cream, sugar, butternut flavoring and 3 1/2 packages of coconut. Add Cool Whip last. Frost layers; use extra coconut on top of layers.

title: north stars(appetizer)
directions: Bake bread at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes in a star bread tube. Remove from the tube.
Cool. Combine cheese, mayonnaise, sour cream and Italian dressing mix. Slice bread into thin slices. Drop about 1 teaspoon on cheese mixture on bread slices.
Sprinkle with peppers. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until slightly crisp. Yields 28 to 32 appetizers.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients well. Pour cornbread mixture into a greased 8-inch pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: frozen pina colada dessert
directions: In a food processor, process the pineapple in 2 batches for 15 seconds each.
Transfer to a 2-quart mixing bowl.
Stir in cream of coconut, orange juice, rum and Triple Sec.
Cover and place in freezer for 24 hours.

title: good for you muffins
directions: Combine egg whites, sugar and oil. In separate bowl, mix dry ingredients. Blend together and mix well. Add milk.
At this point, add 1/2 cup fruit: 1 whole banana, raisins, blueberries or applesauce. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 muffins.

title: hot spiced pineapple juice
directions: Combine juices, sugar and spices in a large pot.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour in rum or extract.
Insert cloves into lemon slices.
Fill cups with the liquid (through a strainer to remove cinnamon pieces) and float a lemon slice on each one for garnish. Makes nine 6-ounce servings.

title: white bean chicken chili
directions: Chop onions and saute in 1/2 butter stick.
After onions are sauteed, melt other 1/2 stick.
In separate bowl, mix chicken broth and flour.
Add to onions, stirring constantly over low heat.
Add half and half, slowly stirring.
After mixture thickens stir in chilies, hot sauce, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture in crock pot; add beans, chopped chicken and cubed cheese.
Leave in crock pot over low for at least 2 hours.
Before stirring, stir in 1/2 c. sour cream.

title: hungarian pork chops
directions: Boil pork chops, then pour onion and cream of mushroom soups over top.
Add potato wedges and brown.
Put cheese on top and melt.

title: hamburger steak
directions: Make hamburger patties.
Saute onions and patties over medium heat.
When patties are done, pour soup over them after draining grease off.
Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fancy pork chops
directions: Brown chops in oil, both sides.
Remove from heat; drain off fat.
Crumble sage over meat; top with onion slices and apples. Sprinkle with wine; cover and cook until not pink in center. Microwave, covered, at High for 3 minutes, then Medium heat for 6 minutes.
Let dish stand for 2 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chili chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken; remove from stock and cut into bite size pieces. Brown bacon in large kettle.
Add potato cubes and stir until coated with bacon drippings.
Add water and stock, tomato sauce, onion and salt.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Place green chilies and grated cheese in 6 soup bowls.
Add chicken.
Spoon hot soup over chicken and garnish with crisp tortilla strips and avocado. Serves 6.

title: christmas ornaments
directions: Blend soda and cornstarch.
Add water.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove and stir for 2 minutes.
Cover with plastic wrap and cool for 15 minutes. Roll out onto wax paper and cut with cookie cutters.
Let dry for 2 days, turning often.

title: baked spiced fruit
directions: Drain fruit, reserving syrup for other uses.
Cut apricots, peaches and pears in half.
Combine fruit in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine the juices and remaining ingredients in a saucepan. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Pour over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cover and chill for 8 hours.
Remove cinnamon stick and whole cloves before serving.

title: cream cheese turnovers
directions: Cream butter or margarine and cream cheese until smooth.
Blend in flour and salt.
Chill dough (keep extra in fridge).
Roll out 1/8-inch thick.
Cut in 2-inch rounds.
Put tiny dab of raspberry and/or apricot preserves.
Fold double and bake at 425° to 450° for about 10 minutes.
Remove hot cookies with a spatula to wire cooling racks and using sifter sift confectioners sugar onto cookies while they are hot (store in refrigerator).

title: cherokee casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain. Add the rest of the ingredients and simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Place in long casserole dish and top with sliced cheese. Bake at 350° until the cheese melts.

title: tortilla dish
directions: *If it seems too hot, use two cans of medium enchilada sauce instead of one can of medium.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and vanilla.
Stir soda in buttermilk and add to mixture.
Then add enough flour to make dough stiff.
Pinch off small amount at a time and place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with your hand; use floured board or dip in flour.
It can also be rolled out and cut.

title: venison jerky
directions: Mix all ingredients except meat.
Cut meat into very thin strips.
Place meat into mixture and refrigerate for 12 hours. After 12 hours, place strips of meat on rack of roasting pan.
Dry in preheated oven for 2 hours at 200°.
Cool and enjoy.

title: creole franks
directions: Cut franks in thin round or long slices. Brown franks, onion and green pepper in skillet with margarine on medium-high heat. Add tomatoes, soup and seasonings; cover. Bring to steaming over high heat; then turn to low for 15 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: pork 'n bean bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, mix sugar, oil, eggs and beans, beating until smooth.
In a separate bowl, combine next 4 ingredients.
Add to bean mixture, stirring just until combined. Stir in raisins and vanilla.
Fill 5 greased and floured 16 ounce cans 2/3 full with batter.
Place cans on a baking sheet and bake 45 to 50 minutes, testing for doneness with a toothpick. Cool completely on a wire rack before removing bread from cans.

title: mud pie
directions: Blend cookies into crumbs; add margarine.
Pat into 9 X 13 cake pan.
Spread softened ice cream on crust.
Drizzle warmed Hershey's fudge topping on top.
Freeze.
Serve with whipped cream and cookie crumbs sprinkled on top.

title: chocolate cream cheese salad
directions: Mix oleo, flour, sugar and nuts well.
(Nuts should be chopped in blender.)
Then press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Cream together the cream cheese, 1 cup Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Put on top of baked crust.
Mix chocolate pudding as directed on the box.
Spread on top of the cheese layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and nuts.

title: cheddar balls
directions: Mix well in large bowl.
Make walnut size balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 8 ingredients.
Add enough flour so that they can be rolled.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.
Use a greased cookie sheet.

title: party broccoli
directions: Saute onion in melted butter or margarine until transparent. Cook and drain broccoli.
Remove onion mixture from heat and stir in all ingredients except broccoli and cashews.
Mix thoroughly. Arrange broccoli on heated platter.
Pour sauce over broccoli and sprinkle cashews on top.

title: homemade pineapple ice cream
directions: Beat eggs at high speed with mixer. Add sugar, vanilla and Pet milk. Stir in pineapple.
Pour mixture into freezer can of a 1 gallon freezer.
Finish with milk. Freeze according to directions. Yields 1 gallon.

title: country butter
directions: Let buttermilk and margarine warm to room temperature. Sprinkle gelatine over cold water in small saucepan and stir constantly over low heat until dissolved and begins to boil, about 3 minutes. Remove from heat. Add buttermilk and salt; stir. Add slowly to beaten margarine. Beat at low speed until all is well blended. Beat on high speed until fluffy and white. Yield: 3 (1-pound) cottage cheese containers. Freezes well.

title: lentil soup
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add rest of ingredients and cook until done, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add eggs and salad oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Spoon into 3 (9-inch) cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool completely.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: weight watchers delight
directions: Tear apart cake and place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer pineapple, bananas, pudding and Cool Whip.

title: happiness cake
directions: Mix this with tears of joy and sorrow.
Flavor with little gifts of love and kindly service.
Fold in prayer, faith and enthusiasm to enlighten the other ingredients and raise the texture to the height of Christian living.
Spread all of this into your daily living.
Bake well with the heart of human kindness.
Serve with a smile at all times to the many people less fortunate than ourselves.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
Drain off water.
Add sweet milk, buttermilk, margarine, cheese and egg.
Add cheese for topping, also.
Bake at 350° until done.
Makes 8 servings.

title: nutted wild rice
directions: Put rice in strainer and run under cold water to rinse thoroughly.
Place rice in heavy saucepan.
Add stock.
Bring to a rapid boil.
Adjust heat to gentle simmer and cook uncovered 45 minutes.
After 30 minutes check for doneness.
It should not be too soft.
Turn rice into colander and drain.
Transfer drained rice to a bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and toss gently.
Let mixture stand for 2 hours to allow flavor to develop.
Serve at room temperature.
Will keep a week refrigerated.
Excellent with beef.

title: meat filled jumbo shells
directions: Cook jumbo shells according to package directions; drain in a single layer on wax paper or aluminum foil to keep shells from sticking together.
Brown beef and pork in skillet; drain. Combine meat, eggs, bread crumbs, Mozzarella cheese, onion, oregano, salt and pepper.
Fill each shell with about 2 tablespoons of the meat filling.
Spread a thin layer of spaghetti sauce on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Place the shells, open side down, in a single layer in the pan.
Cover with the remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Fills about 36 shells.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: cranberry and pineapple salad
directions: Drain crushed pineapple.
Add enough water to pineapple juice to make 1 pint.
Cook cranberries in liquid until they pop.
Take off fire.
Add sugar, Jell-O and pineapple.

title: fudge - 5 pounds
directions: Boil sugar and milk in large pan to full rolling boil. Continue cooking another 10 minutes.
Pour over other ingredients to melt and mix well.
Pour in large baking sheet (or two 9 x 12-inch cake pans).
Cool.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Put in a flowerpot.
Crush up Oreo cookies and put on top.
Garnish with flowers and gummy worms.
Keep cool until ready to eat.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans together and press into bottom of 9 x 13 baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on top of cooled crust.
Spread pie filling on top of this.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush cookies into coarse crumbs.
Reserve 1/4 cup for topping.
To the rest add melted margarine.
Mix well.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream the cheese with electric mixer.
Add sugar and beat well.
Fold in half of Cool Whip.
Spread on crust. Let chill 30 minutes.

title: hot spicy dip
directions: First Layer:
One (16-ounce) can refried beans.

title: crab soup
directions: Saute shallots in oleo for 5 minutes.
Add all other ingredients and bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir often.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute beef in little oil until brown, for 5 minutes.
Add onion soup mix, ketchup and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer over low heat for 1 hour.
Add nutmeg, white wine and sour cream. Serve over rice or noodles with hard rolls and salad.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Heat
oil in large skillet;
blend in flour.
Cook over low heat until dark brown, stirring constantly.
Add tomatoes, onions, okra
and
cups water.
Simmer until tender.
Cook shrimp in shrimp boil as directed on package.
Put all together; add file and simmer another 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add marshmallows, pineapple, bananas and nuts and let congeal until firm. Combine sugar and cream cheese, beating until smooth.
Add Cool Whip.
Spread on top of jello mixture.
Top with coconut and chopped nuts, if desired.

title: congo bars
directions: Pour melted butter over brown sugar.
Mix eggs.
Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Add vanilla; mix in nuts and chips.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Melt the butter in a saucepan.
Add the water and cocoa. Bring to a boil; remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients; beat with mixer until all lumps are out and it is a smooth batter. Pour into a greased cookie sheet pan (17 1/4 x 11 1/4 x 1-inch). Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: coconut muffins
directions: Cream sugar, oleo and then eggs together. Blend in all other ingredients.
Divide evenly into 12 greased muffin pans and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: 6 weeks muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°. Batter will keep for 6 weeks.
Bake only what you need now. Store batter in refrigerator.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Rinse berries and remove stems.
Place them in water, add sugar and boil them lightly until all berries have popped open. Stir frequently to make sure sugar doesn't stick to bottom of the pan.
Cook on medium heat and keep stirring until the sauce has thickened to your preferred consistency
Chill overnight in the refrigerator and serve cold or ladle the hot sauce into clean, hot jars and process pints in a boiling water canner for 15 minutes, half pints for 10 minutes.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare cake and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut half of cake into 1-inch cubes and place in bottom of punch bowl. Cover with 1/2 of the pudding and 1 container of chocolate Cool Whip, then 1 container white Cool Whip.
Top with 2 crushed candy bars or crushed Oreos.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
May top with some candied red cherries for color.
This feeds a crowd!

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix first 11 ingredients.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Shape into pingpong size balls and brown in oil.
Remove and keep warm. Blend flour and seasonings into oil in skillet.
Stir until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat and stir in water.
Heat to boiling. Boil and stir 1 minute.
Reduce heat and stir in sour cream.
Add meatballs and heat through.

title: caramel corn
directions: Place popcorn that has already been popped in a very large bowl and set aside. In a sauce pan bring brown sugar, butter, cream of tartar and syrup to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute. Add baking soda. Beat down the foam. Pour over popcorn and mix to coat. Turn out onto cookie sheet. Place into a 200° oven for 1 hour to let dry.

title: relish
directions: Grind tomatoes; add salt.
Let this mixture drain in a cloth bag overnight.
Grind cabbage, peppers and onions.
Mix everything together and add the vinegar, sugar, celery seed, mustard seed and cloves.
Cook entire mixture until onions are tender, 20 to 25 minutes.
Seal in hot pint jars.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding
and
milk.
Let thicken slightly.	Add 1/2 Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Layer vanilla wafers and bananas in a 9 x 13-inch
baking
dish.
Pour pudding mixture over wafers and bananas and cover with Cool Whip.

title: cheese cake
directions: Set evaporated milk in refrigerator overnight.
Dissolve jello in a cup of hot water; let set at room temperature until it cools. Combine cream cheese and sugar.
Prepare graham cracker crumbs with butter; place in bottom of pan.
With mixer, whip evaporated milk until light and fluffy.
Add cream cheese mixture; mix well. Add jello and vanilla; mix well until fluffy.
Pour onto graham cracker crumbs.
Set in refrigerator for 4 hours, or until set. Top with cherries and enjoy.

title: west virginia joy cake
directions: Make cake according to directions on box. While still hot, pour
crushed pineapple over cake. Let cake cool, then sprinkle instant pudding over it. Mix cream cheese with Cool Whip and beat until smooth. Spread over cake. Sprinkle coconut over top. Refrigerate.

title: pork and celery, greek style
directions: In a large Dutch oven, heat 2 tablespoons oil; brown meat. Add broth, wine, oil and garlic.
Bring to a simmer and cover. Cook for 1 3/4 hours, until tender.
Add celery and simmer 1/2 hour more.
Uncover pot for last 15 minutes to reduce sauce.
Skim off fat.
This can be served with Rice Pilaf or pasta.

title: cathedral windows
directions: Mix chocolate chips and margarine in a saucepan on range over low heat or microwave until chocolate melts.
Remove from heat and cool 10 minutes.
Add 2 slightly beaten eggs and stir.
Cool an additional 10 minutes.
Add pecans and marshmallows.
Stir until well coated.

title: chocolate coconut drops
directions: Put milk, chocolate and salt in top of a double boiler.
Cook over rapidly boiling water, stirring often until thick (about 10 minutes).
Remove from heat and stir in nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on well-greased baking sheet 1 inch apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
These are really sticky cookies and should not be stored in a tight container like Tupperware.

title: perfect baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Scrub potatoes well under cold running water.
Dry thoroughly with paper towels.
With fork, prick skins over entire surface.
(Brush potatoes with salad oil if you like skins soft after baking.)
Place potatoes right on oven rack and bake 50 to 60 minutes or until they are easily pierced with fork or feel soft when squeezed.
Slash an X in top of each potato.
Then, holding potato with pot holders, squeeze ends so steam can escape and potato fluffs up.
Add a pat of butter to each; sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Or top with sour cream, bacon or green onions.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spinach imperial
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain.
Add all other ingredients and put into buttered casserole dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: quick and easy cherry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Combine sugar, flour, milk and baking powder.
Pour in baking dish.
Add cherry pie filling on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and cornmeal; stir in milk and oil. Divide dough into 3 equal portions. Roll each into a 12x9 inch rectangles. Spread 1/3 of sausage over dough, and top with 1/3 cup cheese. Roll up jellyroll fashion, beginning with long side, pinch seam and ends to seal. Wrap in wax paper and chill until firm. Repeat with remaining ingredients. Cut rolls into 1/4 inch slices; place on ungreased mesh wire racks or baking sheets. Bake at 400 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fettucini
directions: Mix butter, sage, basil, garlic salt and white pepper.
Toss cooked noodles (drained) with butter mixture.
Add warmed cream and cheeses and stir gently until cheeses melt.
Sauce gets creamy.
Do not place back on heat.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Saute onion in melted butter.
Stir in flour, seasoned salt and pepper.
Gradually add milk and half and half, stirring constantly.
Arrange a layer of carrots in a 2-quart casserole; place 3 slices of cheese over carrots.
Repeat layers and pour sauce over all.
Top with bread crumbs and bake at 350°, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: classy carrot casserole
directions: Cook sliced carrots in 1 cup water until barely tender. Drain.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Trim excess fat from chops and brown in skillet.
Arrange in casserole dish.
Pour the soup and peas over the top.
Cover and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Do not drain the beans.
Brown 2 pounds beef and drain.
Chop 1 onion and 1 green pepper.
Mix all ingredients in crock-pot and add 1 cup of barbecue sauce.
Cook in crock-pot for 1 hour on High and 2 hours on low.

title: dutch cream waffles
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour and salt.
In a small mixing bowl, beat egg yolks on low while adding cream; beat for 1 minute.
Add to flour mixture; blend on low speed, then beat on medium-high until smooth.
In another small mixing bowl, beat egg whites on high until stiff but not dry.
Gently fold into batter. Bake in a preheated waffle iron according to manufacturer's directions.
Serve with warm maple syrup or fresh fruit in season. Yields 2 to 3 servings.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger; drain and rinse.
Mix in chili seasoning and beans.
Simmer.
In separate pan, cook the tomato juice and the macaroni until partially cooked down.
Mix the macaroni into meat and stir.
Simmer.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients until it resembles cornmeal.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and then stir into buttermilk.

title: nacho casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. In 13 x 9 dish, stir undiluted soup with milk. Spread evenly. Top with half of salsa and half of chips. Carefully spread beans over chips. Top with remaining chips and salsa. Sprinkle with chiles and Cheddar cheese. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until hot. Serves 6.

title: dill pickles
directions: Pack washed, small cucumbers (3 to 4-inches long) as perpendicularly as possible in quart or half-gallon jars.
Before packing cucumbers into jars, put a fresh head of dill in bottom of jar.
Then place one on top.
Put powdered alum in top of each jar.

title: aunt mary starr stuff
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
In large frying pan, saute onion and hamburg until cooked.
Throw in tomato sauce.
When rice is cooked, toss into hamburg mixture.
Mix well.
Season to taste with salt, pepper, Parmesan cheese, basil, parsley, whatever you have.
Serve warm.

title: dream bars
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.	Mix the 1/2 cup butter, 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1 cup flour well.
Put in 9 x 13-inch
pan and bake 15 minutes.
Blend 1 cup brown sugar, baking powder,
vanilla, 1/8 teaspoon salt, well beaten eggs, coconut, 2
tablespoons
flour
and	nuts.
Spread over base. Bake 15 to 20 minutes more.
Cut while warm.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Pour in 2-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mulled cranberry juice
directions: In a saucepan, combined cranberry juice, sugar, cinnamon sticks, cloves and orange rind.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer gently for 12 to 15 minutes.
Strain into a heatproof pitcher.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: overnight cinnamon french toast
directions: In medium bowl, beat everything except bread and butter. Place bread in rimmed pan; pour batter over bread.
Turn bread and coat well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
About 30 to 45 minutes, before serving, make syrup.
In small saucepan, combine all ingredients except cream or evaporated milk.
Bring to a boil; boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in cream.
Cool at least 30 minutes.
Serve warm; refrigerate leftovers.
Fry bread in butter; serve with warm syrup.

title: dirt pie
directions: Beat pudding mix with milk in a large bowl until thickened. Stir in other ingredients.
Mix ingredients well with mixer at low speed.
Layer half the cookie crumbs into a 9 x 13-inch serving dish. Cover with pudding mixture. Top with remaining Oreo crumbs. Chill overnight.
(I freeze mine.)

title: val's famous buns(aka quick and easy yeast rolls)
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, oil, salt and egg.
Stir to dissolve sugar and salt.
Stir in 1 cup flour until smooth. Cover with cloth and place over rack over bowl of hot water.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Stir down.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour; stir until mixed.
Knead 3 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole with chilies
directions: Wash and cut zucchini to 3/4 inch chunks.
Cook until barely tender.
Beat eggs and milk.
Mix and sift dry ingredients; add to milk and egg mix.
Add cubed zucchini, cheese, chopped chilies (remove seeds for milder flavor), parsley and oregano.
Break up 1 slice of bread into egg mixture.
Melt butter and pour on bottom of 2 1/2 quart casserole; break up 1 slice of bread into butter. Pour egg mix over bread in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with salad and French bread.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: egg bake(great breakfast for company.)
directions: Blend eggs, milk, salt and pepper.

Place 6 to 7 slices of sandwich bread (with crust removed) in buttered rectangular dish. Place ham, cheese, mushrooms, onion and green peppers over bread. Pour egg mixture over all. Cover with foil and bake approximately 1 1/4 hours at 300°.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, 1/4 cup cocoa, baking powder and salt in 8-inch square pan.
Add oil and milk.
Stir well.
Sprinkle brown sugar, 1/4 cup cocoa and chips over batter.
Mix vanilla and hot water.
Pour over top and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
The cake will come to the top with pudding on bottom.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Chill 30 minutes. Shape into balls.
Roll in nuts.

title: scalloped potatoes for two(microwave)
directions: Layer potatoes and onion slices alternately in casserole. Sprinkle with salt.
Spoon water over the potato slices.
Dot with margarine.
Cover and microwave on High until almost tender (7 to 8 minutes).
Stir in milk.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika. Microwave uncovered until bubbly, 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together. Boil for 3 minutes. Remove and then stir in the oats, nuts and vanilla. Drop by teaspoon quickly on waxed paper. Delicious!

title: apple butter
directions: Wash and dry apples.
Peel and slice thin.
Lay slices out in sun on cloth-covered table or old window screen.
Cover with another screen or very thin cloth.
This is to keep insects off. Leave in sun all day.
Take inside at night.
If not dry enough, you can put them out the next day.
Usually they will dry in 1 day if the sun is hot and not cloudy.
Put in plastic bag and store in freezer.

title: 7 layer dinner
directions: Place layers in a casserole dish and bake 1 hour or until done.
Cover while baking.

title: 9 day pickles
directions: Scrub pickles and place in salt water strong enough to float an egg.
Let set 3 days.
On the third day, drain and place pickles in clean water and soak three days.
On the sixth day, drain and slice pickles and make a solution of 1 cup vinegar, alum and enough water to cover pickles.
Heat in this solution until water turns green, then drain.
For each 2 gallons of pickles, make syrup of 8 cups of sugar, 1 quart of vinegar, 2 tablespoons whole allspice and 1 1/2 sticks of cinnamon.
Pour syrup over pickles while hot, let stand 3 days then heat pickles in syrup and can in jars.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
You be the judge on mayonnaise. I sometimes add cut up cheese.

title: apple fritters
directions: In deep-fat fryer or deep saucepan, heat 2 inches butter to 375°.
In medium mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, cornstarch, baking powder, salt, allspice, milk, eggs and melted butter.
Stir with fork or wire whisk until just blended.
Fold in apples.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Put all ingredients in first.
Mix, then add water and cook until firm soft ball in water.
Take off heat and add butter the size of walnut.
Let it cool. Start beating. Add vanilla as it gets thicker.
Add 1/2 cup chopped nuts. Beat until it gets glossier, then pour into greased pan and let cool.
Cut into pieces.

title: mock boursin cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender or food processor.
Sprinkle generously with lemon pepper and let stand.
Serve with crackers.

title: pickled beets
directions: Wash beets; leave 6 inches of tops.
Boil in water until you can remove the skin.
Let beets cool; peel off skin.
Put beets in boiling mixture for 10 minutes or so.
Put beets in jars; pour mixture over beets and seal jars.
Process 10 minutes.

title: lomo saltado peru(tenderloin stir-fry)
directions: Cut beef into strips and season.
Cook meat in fat over low heat.
When meat is fairly tender, add sliced onion and pepper, sauteing until nearly cooked.
Add tomatoes, garlic, peas and parsley.
Tomato juice may be added for flavoring is desired. When ready to serve, mix this with some French fries and serve with boiled rice.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Beat butter and peanut butter together until light. Add sugar and brown sugar, creaming well. Add eggs one at a time stirring well after each addition. Add flour, baking powder and salt to mixture, mix well. Add vanilla. Spread mixture in well greased 9 inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: rainbow bars
directions: Mix paste, margarine and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs and extract, then flour and salt.
Line three 9 x 13-inch pans with foil and grease. Divide batter into 3 parts and color one green and one red.
Leave one as is (yellow).
Pour into the 3 pans. Bake these thin layers at 350° for 10 minutes (it may need 12 minutes; don't let it get too hard).

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Bias-slice carrots crosswise about 1/2-inch thick.
Cook, covered, in boiling, salted water, until just tender, 15 to 20 minutes; drain.
Meanwhile, combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and ginger in small saucepan.
Add orange juice, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in butter or margarine.
Pour over hot carrots, tossing to coat evenly. Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: old english prime rib
directions: Select choice prime rib or standing rib.
Season meat with seasonings and rub into the
meat.

title: quick fruit delight
directions: In large bowl, combine fruit.
Mix sour cream and sugar.
Pour over fruit.
Chill 30 minutes in refrigerator.
Put in serving dishes and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Serves 6. May be doubled.

title: special cornbread
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions, being careful to beat air into the mixture.
Mix the rest of the ingredients and gently fold in cake batter.
Pour into 2 greased 8-inch pie pans or a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven until lightly browned.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti, drain.
Stir butter in while hot, stir in Parmesan and eggs.
Form crust in 10-inch pie plate of spaghetti mixture.
In skillet cook ground beef, onion and green pepper. Drain.
Stir in tomatoes and tomato paste, sugar, oregano and salt. Heat thoroughly.
Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti.
Fill with tomato mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake 5 minutes longer or until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: cajun roast
directions: You will also need one large cooking bag.

title: lazy day apple dessert
directions: Cut up apples.
Lay in 6 x 10-inch Pyrex dish and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Mix together next 5 ingredients.
Add egg to this mixture.
Beat with fork and then fingers.
Pat over apples.
Melt oleo and drizzle over dry mixture.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Enjoy.

title: honest to goodness maidrites
directions: Add onion to meat and brown.
Mix rest of ingredients and add to meat mixture.
Steam 5 minutes.
Serve warm on a bun.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in shortening.
Add soups and water; mix well.
Add rice and blend thoroughly.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover and sprinkle buttered breadcrumbs on top.
Bake for 15 more minutes or until rice is tender.

title: easy quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased quiche dish or pie pan.
Cook at 375° until set.

title: tex-mex casserole
directions: In a big skillet, brown meat and drain off fat.
Mix chili powder with meat, then add the prepared rice.
Mix and put in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Sprinkle the black olives on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Put into baking dish; add soup (no water).
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 375° until biscuits are done.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saut green peppers, onions and garlic in olive oil. Add a splash of water and cook until soft. Add brown sugar, pepper, thyme, cayenne pepper and bay leaf. Stir well. Stir in tomatoes and cook over low heat for 30 minutes or until sauce is thick. Add mushrooms and cook for a few more minutes. Mix in parsley and shrimp and cook for 5 to 10 minutes or until the shellfish is cooked thoroughly. Serve immediately so shrimp won't overcook. Serve over rice. Serves 6.

title: bread pudding
directions: Cut bread or cake into cubes and put into casserole dish.
Beat 3 egg yolks plus 1 whole egg (reserve 3 egg whites).
Add sugar, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour over bread, making sure all cubes are covered.
Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes or until set.
Take out and cover with fruit.
Beat egg whites until stiff, adding 2 teaspoons sugar.
Cover fruit with this meringue and return casserole to oven for approximately 10 to 15 minutes or until meringue is golden brown.

title: beef quisado
directions: Heat a deep frying pan and add oil.
Put in garlic and stir. Add cabbage, onions and bell peppers. Saute a few minutes.
Add shredded, cooked stew meat. Add can of tomatoes and 3/4 c. water and soy sauce. Cover and simmer for about 2 hours.
Serve over cooked rice. The longer you cook, the better the flavor.

title: microwave devil's food cake
directions: With electric mixer, cream the sugar and butter.
Add egg and water.
Stir in remaining ingredients; blend until smooth.
Into greased round 8-inch baking dish, pour batter.
Heat 7 to 9 minutes, giving dish 1/4 turn every 3 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 10 minutes.
Store covered until ready to serve. Makes 1 layer.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese; add salsa.
Mix well.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: krispie treats
directions: Bring sugar and corn syrup to boil.
Remove from heat.
add peanut butter to syrup mixture and stir until dissolved.
Then add Rice Krispies.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, peanut butter and powdered sugar; blend until creamy. Add vanilla and Cool Whip. Mix well. Pour into crust. Garnish with cashews, caramel syrup or whipped cream. Chill. Very rich.

title: cloud nine biscuits
directions: Mix sugar, salt and 2 cups flour with shortening until crumbly; add egg and milk.
Mix together lightly; add rest of flour (if needed) to make soft dough.
Knead gently 2 or 3 strokes; pat out to 3/4-inch height.
Cut; bake close together for soft biscuits or far apart for crusty ones.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cherry icebox pie
directions: Fold whipped cream into beaten milk and lemon juice.
Add nuts and cherries and put in cooled baked pie shell.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Pour pie filling in bottom of pan.
Mix milk, eggs and melted butter good.
Pour this over filling.
Mix flour, brown sugar and butter together (this will be crumbly).
Stir in oatmeal and pour over top.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate the mild Cheddar, onion and garlic clove together.
Then mix all other ingredients together.
Roll up into one huge ball. Then roll into nuts of choice.

title: cinnamon fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours to blend flavors.
Serve with fruit.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with apple wedges.

title: strawberry cream cake roll
directions: Line a greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jellyroll pan with wax paper.
Lightly grease waxed paper.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs until light and lemon colored.
Gradually add sugar and beat until very light and thick.
Beat in water and vanilla.
Sift cake flour, baking powder and salt together.
Fold into egg-sugar mixture.
Pour batter into jellyroll pan and spread evenly.
Bake in a 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until cake springs back when pressed in the center.
Lightly sift confectioners sugar onto a sheet of waxed paper or a towel.
Turn while baking and trim dry edges from the cake.
Roll cake up with towel or paper, starting at one of the long sides and cool.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: In large bowl cream butter, sugar, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients; blend on low speed until a stiff dough forms (about 1 minute).
Shape into balls or bars covered with crushed Heath bars and bake 5 to 15 minutes or until done at 350°.
Nuts and crushed candy bars may be stirred into dough before baking.

title: cousin barb's cauliflower salad
directions: Mix together cauliflower, lettuce, pepper, onion and peas. Place 1/2 of salad in bowl. Sprinkle 1/2 package dry seasoning mix over.
Spread 1 cup of mayonnaise over this (do not use salad dressing).
Repeat with second half of salad, seasoning mix and 1 cup mayonnaise.
Top with crumbled bacon.
Sprinkle with as much Parmesan cheese as you like.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Toss before serving.
Can be made ahead and keeps for days.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in frying pan with 2 tablespoons fat. Drain off fat.
Add green pepper, catsup and sugar.
Mix vinegar and dry mustard in small cup until dissolved.
Add to hamburger mixture.
Simmer 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: venison enchiladas
directions: Cut into pieces and cook in crock-pot with one can of cream of mushroom soup until it comes off the bone easily.
Roll in plain flour.
Then fry in small amount of vegetable oil until crisp on the outside.

title: brown bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Steam in well-greased tube pan until firm.
Brown in 350° oven.

title: strawberries romanoff
directions: Gently wash berries in cold water.
Drain on paper towels; hull.
Turn into serving bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar and Cointreau; toss.
Chill 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Let frozen yogurt soften in refrigerator about 1 hour.
Make Dream Whip with skim milk and vanilla as package directs.
Fold in almond extract. Gently fold in Dream Whip, softened yogurt and strawberries together.
Serve at once in stemmed dessert goblets.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: brandied cranberry sauce
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients to boiling.
Simmer, uncovered, until berries pop.
Stir together cornstarch and water.
Stir into berry mixture.
Cook until thickened and cook 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Stir in brandy.
Store in refrigerator or freeze. Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: beet pickles
directions: Choose small beets; boil until tender.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix milk, mayonnaise and sugar. Add flour and stir well. Bake in greased muffin tins at 450° until brown. Makes 12 rolls.

title: soup-er meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in dish and bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: To eggs, add sugar, butter, corn meal, vanilla, vinegar and nutmeg, stirring until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Butter tops and bottoms of rolls.
Sprinkle garlic salt, then Parmesan, then parsley flakes.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes (until brown).
Serve warm.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix the first 3 items together in a skillet.
Boil for 3 minutes, until thick.
Take off burner.
Add the jello; mix well. Add the strawberries when slightly cooled.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: yum-yum's
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg.
Press in bottom of pan. Mix confectioners sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs.
Pour this mixture on top of other ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: lasagna spinach roll-ups
directions: Cook lasagna according to package directions.
In saucepan, cook onion and garlic in hot oil until tender.
Add tomato sauce, basil and oregano.
Bring to a boil and simmer 20 minutes.

title: old-fashioned chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt, cornstarch, flour and cocoa; gradually add milk and stir well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir a little of the mixture into egg yolks; blend yolks into hot mixture.
Boil 1 minute; remove from heat.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Pour into pie shells.
Add meringue; bake until done.
Yield: 2 (8-inch) pies.

title: allison's spinach salad(servings:  4)
directions: Mix together bacon, onions and spinach.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten egg.
Add flour and spices. Add to margarine mixture.
Add vanilla, diced apples and nuts. Stir well.
Put in an 8-inch round baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt one stick of margarine.
Add cake mix in small amounts, using a fork to make it of crunchy consistency.

title: dave's stuffed peppers
directions: Parboil rice.
Combine all ingredients into large bowl and mix well by hand.
Poke bottom of peppers with two pronged fork. Place mixture into peppers and bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°. You can add shredded cheese to top before serving.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Makes about 5 cups.
Serve hot or chilled.

title: 7-up pie crust
directions: Add flour and salt; cut in Crisco.
Add 7-Up.
Mix well; pour out on floured board.
Let rest for 10 minutes.
Work together a couple minutes and roll out into pie shells.
Makes 4 to 5 (9-inch) crusts.
Dough may be frozen.

title: orange ambrosia
directions: Mix jello, cream the cottage cheese and pineapple and fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until completely chilled.

title: fudge
directions: Heat first 3 ingredients until boiling and cook for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients to it.
Let it cool, then cut into squares.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Pour cake mix in mixer bowl.
Empty lemon Jell-O in cake mix. Mix well.
Pour oil and nectar in and start mixer.
Add eggs 1 at a time.
After each egg, beat 1 minute.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: turkey kidney bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss lightly.
Chill at least 1 hour to blend flavors.
Yields 6 (1/2-cup) servings and contains about 205 calories per serving.

title: meat loaf
directions: Have all visible fat trimmed from beef and veal, then have it ground once or do it yourself.
Mix the meat with all remaining ingredients.
Shape into a loaf and place in a lightly oiled baking pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 50 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: old time buttermilk pie
directions: Cream soft butter with sugar.
Add eggs and flour; beat well. Stir
in buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and sprinkle 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg on top of pie.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool before serving.
Time of preparation: 40 to 50 minutes.

title: sausage stuffed squash
directions: Place squash, cut side down, in roasting pan.
Add water (about 1/4-inch).
Bake at 400° about 25 minutes.
Turn cut side up and brush with butter.
Saute sausage, onion and celery until lightly browned.
Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients into squash halves.
Bake at 350° until tender to fork.

title: nuns farts with sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Mix all ingredients well.
Roll the dough and butter it.
Roll as a jelly roll and cut 1/2 inch thick.
Place in a 9 x 11 pan.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes, then up the temperature to 500° to brown.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda and salt in a large bowl.
Stir in carrots, apple, coconut, raisins, nuts and pineapple.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add the lard.
Shape into cookies. Bake in a 350° oven until brown.

title: frozen banana salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl in order given.
Mix well after each addition.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Freeze until firm.
Yields 12 servings.

title: ranch cookies
directions: Blend oil and sugar (will not be "creamed" like shortening). Add eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add flour sifted with salt, soda and baking powder.
Add cornflakes, oatmeal, coconut (and raisins and nuts, if desired).
Batter will be very stiff, it takes muscles to stir all ingredients to mix thoroughly!
Drop by teaspoonful on baking sheet and bake in preheated oven at 350°. Should bake in 8 to 9 minutes.
Makes at least 3 dozen.

title: boiled frosting
directions: Boil brown sugar and water in covered dish.
Do not stir.
Let it boil until syrupy.
Dip fork until it spins a thread.
Have egg whites beaten stiff.
Pour syrup over egg whites, beating constantly to desired consistency.
Add vanilla.

title: moist cranberry-apple cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugars.
Beat in egg and milk.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Stir into butter mixture until well blended.
Stir in orange rind, apples and cranberries.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheets. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: polvorones(a cookie)
directions: Cream butter, 1/2 cup confectioners sugar and almond flavoring. Combine flour, pecans and salt and stir into butter mixture.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Have ready a plastic bag containing one-half box confectioners sugar.
As cookies come from oven, drop 2 to 3 at a time into bag to coat with sugar.
Place on rack.
Cool one half hour.
Repeat coating process.
Let sit overnight.
These are called Mexican Wedding Cakes.
Delicious.

title: fruit pops
directions: Using electric mixer, beat all ingredients together.
Pour into paper cups.
Insert plastic spoons upside down in each cup. Freeze until firm.
One quarter cup sugar may be added before freezing.

title: vi's molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, molasses and egg.
Beat well.
Sift together flour and dry ingredients.
Add to first mixture.
Form into balls.
Roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes on greased cookie sheet.
Makes 36.

title: paella(spain)
directions: In a large saucepan, brown sausage links and cut in 1/4-inch slices.
Add minestrone soup, tomato sauce, thyme and garlic powder; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 3 minutes.
Add shrimp and chicken.
Simmer, covered, until shrimp are pink and chicken is cooked through, about 5 minutes.
Stir in uncooked rice.
Remove from heat.
Cover; let stand until almost all the liquid is absorbed.
Serve in bowls.
Makes 6 cups.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix raisins and nuts with dry ingredients.
In separate bowl, cream the butter.
Add sugar slowly; keep mixing.
Add egg.
Add dry ingredients to butter mixture, alternating with applesauce.
Mix well after each addition and turn into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: ike's cinnamon cookies
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar and butter.
Add and mix flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Now, chill approximately 1 hour.

title: fresh raspberry crisp(may use other berries or fruit of your choice.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place fruit in bottom of 9-inch square baking pan and sprinkle sugar over fruit.
In medium bowl, blend together margarine, flour, brown sugar and oats until it resembles a coarse meal.
Sprinkle over fruit.
Bake for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve hot.
Makes 9 servings.

title: one-two-three cake
directions: Cream shortening in a bowl.
Add sugar gradually, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla, beating well after each addition.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cakes test done.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes before removing to racks to cool completely.
Spread Pineapple Filling between layers.

title: fundough
directions: For a brown crust on chicken, rub mayonnaise generously over the skin before cooking.

title: dump-it-cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump sweetened applesauce into pan. Dump crushed pineapple on top of that.
Spread dry yellow cake mix over that.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Combine oil, molasses, white sugar and egg; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
This will be hard to mix.
Form into 1-inch balls, roll in granulated sugar and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° 8-10 minutes.
We like ours soft, so I take them out before the bottom gets too brown.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together in order given.
Sift together remaining ingredients and add to first mixture.
Bake almost 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: date yummies
directions: Stir together in pan.
Cook until mixture is thick.
Stir until mixture has cooled to a warm state.
Drop teaspoon in bowl of coconut and roll.
Place on wax paper to completely cool.
So quick and so "yummy."

title: roasted pecans
directions: In a jar, mix sugar, vinegar and pecans.
Shake together well to coat pecans.
Spread on aluminum in a shallow pan.
Bake in preheated 250° oven for 45 minutes.
Add butter and sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Stir well and bake 30 minutes more.

title: fruit cake(easy and good)
directions: Use a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix egg, flour, milk and shortening.
Roll out and cut in 2-inch squares. In a pot, heat broth and drop in dough and chicken.
Cook for a half hour.
This makes a hard dumpling.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cream sugars and oleo.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and oatmeal.
Cut orange slices with 1/4 cup flour on board, coating.
Fold into cookie batter with coconut.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon and drain on paper towel.
Pour off grease.
Brown onion in same pan.

title: chicken casserole(also seafood)
directions: Mix and put in quart casserole.
Top with 8 ounce Pepperidge Farm stuffing mixed with 1/4 pound oleo.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Reduce cooking time 1/2 hour for seafood.

title: irish cream
directions: Blend together in a blender until frothy.
Refrigerate.
Makes 1 quart.

title: pea and almond salad
directions: Combine peas, almonds, celery and green onions.
Combine sour cream and mayonnaise.
Fold mixture into pea salad to coat evenly. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: jack's crock-pot chili
directions: Brown ground lean beef in a large pan.
Saute onion and peppers.
Add all ingredients to crock-pot.
Cook on high for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Turn to medium for 3 hours.
Cook on low for one hour.
Add chili powder to taste.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Add flour and salt.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick and cut.
Add 1/2 pecan to each, if desired.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes.

title: easy fruit cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes. Cool and wrap good. Store in refrigerator.
Yummy.

title: scampi
directions: Combine butter, oil, lemon juice, vermouth, garlic, salt, pepper and parsley in a blender.
Mix.
Arrange shrimp in a 9 x 13-inch oblong dish.
Pour mixture over shrimp.
Let set for one hour.
Sprinkle green onions and Parmesan cheese on top.
Broil 5 minutes.
Turn shrimp and broil 2 minutes.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mash avocado with fork and blend in tomato.
Add other ingredients.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: peachy lemonade punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water in large container.
Add lemonade concentrate and remaining water, mix well.
Chill thoroughly.
Pour over ice in punch bowl and serve. Makes 40 (4 oz.) servings.

title: hilda's famous fried chicken
directions: On Thanksgiving Day our house is always packed with relatives and friends.
I usually cook the dinner, but then everyone who comes also brings a dish.
Needless to say, the turkey is not the only one stuffed that day.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Combine with remaining ingredients and add salt and pepper to taste.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Grate 1/4 cup additional cheese, if desired, and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli spread
directions: Cook celery and onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients in saucepan and cook until cheese is melted.
Spread on Melba rounds.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix flour, egg yolks and milk. Beat well. Add butter and cook in double boiler until thick. Add flavoring. Pour in baked pie shell. Top with meringue made of beaten egg whites and sugar. Put in oven and brown top.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Stir all ingredients and bake at 350 degrees for 55 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream the softened ingredients in food processor.
Add all ingredients except flour.
Pulse until blended.
Remove to bowl and add flour.
Put dough in cookie press fitted with star plate. Press onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Boil raisins and water 5 minutes.
Cool.
Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and raisin mixture.
Grease seven No. 2 tin cans.
Fill half full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool a few minutes on rack, then remove from cans.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix together a cold syrup; do not heat.
Sterilize 4 pint jars.
Put sliced onions evenly into jars and enough cucumbers to fill jars.
Stir syrup well; pour into jars to cover onions and cucumbers.
Screw on lids and seal.
Refrigerate five days before using.
Will keep in refrigerator 9 months to 1 year.

title: caesar salad
directions: Rinse and drain the beans.
Combine all ingredients. Refrigerate overnight.
Serve chilled with crackers.

title: honey-mustard pork salad
directions: In a small bowl or custard cup, stir together the 1 tablespoon honey, 2 teaspoons Dijon mustard and 1/8 teaspoon ginger. Trim fat from pork tenderloin. Place on a rack in a shallow foil-lined roasting pan. Brush mustard mixture over outside of tenderloin. Insert a meat thermometer in center of tenderloin. Roast, uncovered, in a 425° oven for 25 to 35 minutes or until thermometer registers 160°.

title: red molded salad or dessert
directions: Mix together and put on top of set Jell-O.
Let set for 5 minutes and add rest of Jell-O.
Let set until firm.

title: party mix
directions: Mix first six ingredients together.
Then mix last four ingredients together and pour over cereal mixture and mix.
Place in large shallow pan and bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: italian roast beef
directions: Add all ingredients into covered dish and cook roast in oven at 350° until tender.
As roast cooks, cut into smaller pieces (it speeds the cooking process).
Once it is tender, take roast out of oven; remove bay leaf and pull meat apart.
Put into crock-pot. Simmer.
May need to add more water.

title: jennifer's favorite(student favorite)
directions: Put chicken in ungreased baking dish.
Mix soup, sour cream and wine together.
Spread over chicken.
Sprinkle onions over evenly, then cover with cheese.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: fortune cookies
directions: Take time out to write or type up some fortunes on 1/2 inch X 2 inch strips of paper.
Sift together flour, cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Add oil and egg white.
Beat until smooth.
Beat in water and vanilla.
Drop batter by level teaspoons onto a well greased baking sheet.
Smooth out with back of oiled spoon to make 4 inch circles.
Bake at 300 degrees until light golden brown.
If underbaked, the cookies will tear.
Cookies will be extremely hot. Use gloved hands, if possible.
Immediately, after you take out of oven, place a fortune in the bottom half of the cookie.
Take a wide spatula and take top half of cookie and fold over to make a 1/2 circle.
Lift cookie up and take both sides and bend toward the middle.
Place upside down, with points in the bottom, in an empty muffin pan and let cool.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed.
Set aside.
Crumble bread.
Mix ground beef, sausage, egg, bread and 1/2 cup ketchup in a bowl.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Split meat mix in half. Spread 1/2 meat mix on bottom and up the sides of loaf pan.
Pour macaroni and cheese in middle.
Spread second half of meat mix on top of macaroni and cheese.
Connect with sides.
Pour 1 cup ketchup on top.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: roast pork with yams and white onions
directions: Trim excess fat from meat.
Rub with salt and pepper.
Put on rack in shallow baking pan.
Roast in preheated slow oven (325°) for 35 to 40 minutes to the pound or until meat thermometer registers 185°.
Arrange yams and onions on rack beside pork. Bake for 15 minutes longer, basting frequently with apple juice. Garnish serving platter with spiced pears, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vegetable bean stew
directions: In 4-quart saucepan or Dutch oven, combine all ingredients; mix well. Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Cover; simmer 45 to 55 minutes or until vegetables and lentils are tender. Makes 5 servings.

title: nearly sinful devil's delight cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
After removing from oven, punch holes all over cake.
When completely cool, top with whipped topping and sprinkle with candy bars.
Keep refrigerated.

title: rich chocolate fudge
directions: In large saucepan over medium-high heat, combine sugar, butter and evaporated milk.
Cook 10 to 14 minutes or until mixture comes to full boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to medium; stirring occasionally, boil 6 to 7 minutes or until candy thermometer reaches 228° or small amount of mixture dropped into ice water forms a 2-inch soft thread.
Remove from heat; gradually stir in marshmallow cream until well blended; stir in vanilla. Spread mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cool completely at room temperature.
To serve, cut into 1-inch squares.
Store in cool place.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Combine vinegar, water and spices in saucepan. Bring to the boil and simmer for 1 to 2 minutes. Pour over eggs. Cool; place in jar and refrigerate. Ready to eat the second day.

title: cranberry crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Toss cranberries, sugar and walnuts in 1 1/2-quart baking dish. In another bowl, combine flour, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in butter with pastry blender.
Cover cranberries with flour/sugar mix.
Bake 45 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.
Yields 6 servings.

title: hot spiced wine
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients in small saucepan for 5 minutes. Strain syrup into a small bowl.
Combine the remaining ingredients in a large saucepan and bring to a simmer.
Remove from heat. Stir in syrup; pour in punch bowl and garnish with slices of oranges and lemons, melon balls and strawberries.
Serve in mugs with a cinnamon stick.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan and add milk and pepper.
Stir frequently, allowing mixture to simmer gently.
Cook fettucini according to directions on package.
Combine fettucini and sauce in a heated mixing bowl.
Toss gently, gradually adding cheese until mixture has a creamy texture.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: baked sausages
directions: Put sausages at bottom of Dutch oven or heavy baking dish. Spread sliced onions over sausages.
Spread apples over onions to cover.
Pack brown sugar over top.
Bake, covered, at 300° for 3 1/2 hours.
Remove most of apple and onions and drain off most of liquid before serving.
Cut sausages in half.
Serve in chafing dish with toothpicks or cocktail forks.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Beat egg yolks. Combine all ingredients in a pot and bring to a boil on the stove. Stir continually until it thickens, then take off and put in baked pie shell.
Beat whites of eggs and put on top. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: o.c.'s hot dip
directions: Puree all ingredients in a blender, then cook on low, uncovered, until most of the liquid evaporates and leaves a thick dip.
This may take a couple of hours, but can be speeded up by cooking on a higher temperature.
Stir occasionally to avoid scorching.
A crock-pot works best for this.

title: golden cake
directions: Beat egg yolks and water until thick.
Add sugar gradually; beat until fluffy.
Add salt to flour and then add gradually to yolks.
Add vanilla; beat well.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff.
Fold egg whites into yolks carefully.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: orange jello mold
directions: Mix Jell-O with one cup hot water and the juice from oranges. Add sherbet and oranges.
Mix well.
Pour into mold; chill until firm.
Unmold onto lettuce leaves and garnish with additional oranges, if desired.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, onions, green peppers and frozen peas.
Mix sugar, mayonnaise and sour cream.
Spread over layered vegetables. Sprinkle with bacon bits.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Chill.

title: baked fruit with sour cream
directions: Drain fruit, saving 1/2 cup juice.
Arrange fruit in 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Put strawberries on top.
Sprinkle brown sugar on.
Pour juice and rum over.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with sour cream when served.

title: brunch pie
directions: Mix and press into pie pan, make sides high.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: hot nachos
directions: Spread each nacho chip with bean dip.
Top with grated onion and cheese.
Place a strip of jalapeno on top of each chip.
Bake in 400° oven until cheese has melted.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix, cover and chill.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Spray 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray. Spoon mix into pan and press down lightly.
Bake 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Invert on serving platter.
Makes 8 servings with 135 calories and 5 grams fat.

title: frozen lemonade pie
directions: Beat milk.
Add lemonade directly from freezer and beat until very thick.
Fold in topping.
Pour into crust and refrigerate.

title: cheese cake pie
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature (or warm in microwave).
Mix softened cream cheese and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip, mixing well.
Spoon into prepared crust.
Chill 4 to 6 hours.
If desired, top with blueberry, cherry, strawberry, pineapple, etc. Pie filling is quick, easy and good.

title: sour cream chicken(serves 6)
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over chicken breasts.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle breadcrumbs lightly over the chicken and bake for one hour in a 350° oven (covered for 45 minutes/uncovered for 15 minutes).

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, oleo and milk together; bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Add nuts and cocoa, if desired.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: graham cracker fudge
directions: Boil 1 minute the margarine, sugar, cocoa, salt and milk. Take off heat.
Add peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla. Mix well; do not beat.
Add graham crackers and mix.
Pour into pan.

title: ritz pie
directions: Using low speed on mixer, add sugar to egg whites.
Then fold in Ritz crackers and nuts.
Pour into a 9-inch pie pan, pushing to edge and up a little higher than center.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each one.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream, beating until smooth. Pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Let stand on cooling rack for 5 to 10 minutes; turn out of pan to cool.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Split English muffins.
Spread 1 tablespoon of sauce on half of muffin.
Top with cheese and whatever other toppings you choose.
Put muffins on a cookie sheet covered with foil.
Bake in oven at 400° for a few minutes until cheese is hot and bubbles.

title: sausage and lentil casserole
directions: Cover lentils with water and salt.
Cover and cook over high heat.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer until tender.
Add water, if necessary.
Slit the casing of the sausage lengthwise and remove it.
Slice the meat 1/2-inch thick; set aside.

title: agression cookies
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl.
With hands mash, knead and squeeze to well mixed firm dough.
Form into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Dip bottom of greased small water glass in granulated sugar and flatten each ball.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 15 dozen cookies.

title: rosalyn carter's date nut roll
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan.
Add dates, nuts, sugar and salt.
Cook for 8 minutes over low heat.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and cereal.
Cool until mixture can be worked with hands.
Shape into finger-sized rolls or walnut-sized balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Fry meats together; drain fat.
Put in Dutch oven.
Add seasonings, onion, peppers, Ragu, tomato paste and tomato sauce. Simmer all day.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar before serving.

title: coke dessert
directions: Mix reserved juices; bring to a boil.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Stir in Coke; add pineapple, cherries and cream cheese. Pour into oblong cake pan; refrigerate until set.

title: egg yolk pastry
directions: Combine dry ingredients; cut in lard.
Place yolks in measuring cup and stir with fork until smooth.
Blend in enough cold water to make scant cupful.
Sprinkle gradually over dry ingredients.
Toss with fork to make a soft dough.
Roll out as usual.

title: smorgasbord meatballs
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in a large skillet.
Add onion; saut 1 to 2 minutes, until tender.
In large bowl of electric mixer, combine bread crumbs and water; let stand 1 to 2 minutes. Add beef, sausage, onion, salt, allspice, white pepper and sugar. Beat with mixer on low speed until smooth.
Chill, if needed.
Use teaspoons to shape meat into tiny meatballs.
Pour melted butter for frying 1/4-inch deep in large skillet.
Add meatballs and brown on all sides.
Drain on towels.
Arrange in serving dish and pour hot soup over meatballs when ready to serve.

title: peach delight
directions: Mix 2 cups flour, margarine and chopped nuts together.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip together.
Spread over crust.
Put in refrigerator until you are ready to spread fruit on it.
Spread fruit over crust.
Mix sugar, flour, peach Jell-O and water.
Cook over medium heat until thick and clear.
Cool a few minutes.
Spread over other ingredients.

title: oriental noodle and chicken salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in large bowl.
Shake together oil, sugar, seasoning packet and vinegar.

title: hamburger bake
directions: Brown ground meat, onion, green pepper and salt.
Add tomato sauce, garlic, salt and oregano.
Mix cream cheese, cottage cheese and sour cream together.
Spread noodles evenly in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Add cheese mixture; spread evenly.
Add meat mixture evenly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Fill crescent rolls with chicken and cheese.
Mix soup and milk; pour over rolls.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: twelve minute frosting *
directions: Cook in double boiler for 12 minutes, beating the entire 12 minutes with egg beater.
After beating the 12 minutes, beat until cool and spread.

title: cheesy broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli; stir soup and milk, then add remaining ingredients to soup.
Put in casserole and sprinkle with crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, slice cheese in 1/4 inch strips and place over tops of each piece of chicken.
Cover all with soup. Spread stuffing mix over chicken and pour melted butter over all. Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: aunt twila's bacon waffles
directions: Cook bacon; crumble, then set aside.
Mix all other ingredients in large bowl.
Pour batter in waffle iron; sprinkle with bacon.

title: chipmunk pie(sugar free or with sugar)
directions: Beat eggs and sugar. Add flour with baking powder and salt. Add apples and nuts. Bake in greased pie pan at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: noodles parmesan
directions: Cook noodles using package directions; drain.
Add butter; mix well.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and sour cream.

title: tangy salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; cool.
Soften cream cheese with pineapple and banana.
Add pecans, then jello and fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: chicken divan
directions: Mix soup, Miracle Whip, cheese and curry powder to make sauce.

title: biscuits
directions: Take large bowl and
sift 3/4 full of flour.
Make hole in center.
Pour
buttermilk
into
hole;
add
