salt, soda and baking powder. Stir slowly, adding flour until stiff enough to handle with hands (not too stiff).
Pinch off small amount and roll out in	palms of hands, placing in greased iron skillet. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine and graham crackers and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs, remaining margarine and confectioners sugar for 15 minutes with mixer.
Spread mixture over cracker crumbs.
Place sliced bananas on top of crumbs.
Spread pineapple over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Sprinkle the top with nuts and arrange cherries on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli-rice melange
directions: Combine cooked rice and broccoli.
Mix egg, onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt and milk.
Stir into the rice-broccoli mixture.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with melted butter and shredded cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Mix margarine, Crisco, sugar and egg yolks; beat until fluffy. Add flour, soda and buttermilk alternately.
Add coconut, pecans and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Fold into mixture. Pour into three 8-inch greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pan saver
directions: Mix together and store in airtight container in refrigerator. Use whenever recipe calls for greased and floured baking pans. Will keep indefinitely.

title: minestrone soup
directions: In Dutch oven, combine beef, water and salt.
Cover; cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil (10 to 12 minutes). Reduce heat to low.
Continue cooking until meat is tender (about 1 hour).

title: killer bread
directions: Slice bread in half, lengthwise.
Soften cream cheese (room temperature).
Mix cream cheese and sour cream together; add Good Seasons herb garlic.
Mix well.
Spread cream cheese mixture on bread; top with Mozzarella.
Broil in oven until cheese is melted and bubbly (lite brown), but don't burn.
Cut in slices and serve hot.
Can be served as an appetizer or with the meal.

title: old-fashioned vegetable beef-barley soup
directions: Place beef shanks in shallow roasting pan.
Roast, uncovered, at 400° for 1 hour.
Transfer shanks to large soup kettle, scraping up juices from bottom of roasting pan and adding to kettle.
Add onion, celery and water.
Bring to boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low.
Partially cover and cook with lid slightly ajar, skimming off foam that rises to top, 2 1/2 hours.
After boiling beef 2 1/2 hours, remove and cut into serving size pieces.
Add carrots, leeks, parsnips, turnips, bouquet garni, tomatoes and salt and pepper, if desired.
Simmer, partially covered, 30 minutes. Add barley and simmer partially covered 30 minutes longer.
Remove bouquet garni; taste and adjust seasonings, if desired.
Makes 4 quarts of soup.

title: frozen cukes
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions and salt.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Wash and drain.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Return to refrigerator for 24 hours.
Spoon into containers.
Cover with juice and freeze.

title: french strawberry glaze pie
directions: Clean strawberries.
Simmer 1 cup strawberries and 2/3 cup water about 3 minutes.
Blend sugar and cornstarch (sifted) with remaining water.
Add to boiling mixture.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Spread cream cheese over coated pie shell. Save 1/2 cup choice strawberries.
Put remaining 2 1/2 cups strawberries in baked pie shell.
Cover with cooked mixture. Garnish with remaining berries.
Refrigerate until firm, approximately 2 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: applesauce cake with raisins
directions: Sift flour, spices and soda together. Cream Crisco; beat in eggs, sugar, nuts and raisins (that have been cooked in small amount of water, approximately 1/3 cup and 1/3 cup sugar called for in recipe). Add flour and applesauce alternately. Cook in tube pan for 1 hour at 300°; let cool.
Ice with Burnt Sugar Icing.

title: yogurt cake
directions: Line a 9-inch square cake pan with greased wax paper.
Dissolve cocoa in boiling water and stir in baking soda.
Let cool.
Beat corn oil and sugar well and add eggs, one at a time, beating well before each addition.
Sift in flour and salt and fold alternately with yogurt.
Stir in cooled chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cake can be eaten plain or with cream.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add enough sour cream to make dip creamy.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together; stir in flour.
Place 2/3 of batter on large cookie sheet; spread 1 large can of pie filling and drop remaining batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: brownie cupcakes
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Combine the rest of the ingredients and blend until smooth.
Fill small baking cups a little over half full and bake for 25 minutes at 325°.
Cool and dust with powdered sugar.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt margarine; add cocoa
and the rest of the ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: real corn bread
directions: Beat all ingredients together and bake in a well-greased bread pan at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: rhoda sandwiches
directions: Mix well and serve on wheat or rye bread.
Make sandwiches and cut in fourths.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Keeps well for a few days.

title: tropicana twister holiday punch
directions: In an 8-quart punch bowl, combine twister and ginger ale.
Add small scoops of ice cream.
Makes 24 (8 ounce) servings.

title: poppy cock
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly and store in airtight jar or container.

title: custard
directions: Place mandarin sections in a single layer in the bottom of 6 individual ramekin dishes.
Scald milk and pour over beaten egg yolks, stirring constantly until blended.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt, mix with egg mixture.
Cook mixture in a double boiler until thick, about 7 minutes.
Fill ramekins with custard.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve cold.
Serves 6.

title: quick baked hash browns
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in hash browns and mix all ingredients except cornflakes and 1/4 cup margarine.
Pour mixture over hash browns.
Mix cornflakes and margarine.
Sprinkle on mixture and bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.
Top with sliced black olives.

title: sweet jammies
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Butter muffin tins.
Blend dry ingredients in bowl.
Melt butter.
Off heat, stir in yogurt and milk and when smooth, beat in egg and vanilla.
Add butter mixture to dry ingredients and stir well.
Spoon half the batter into muffin cups.
Place about a teaspoon of jam over batter in each cup and top with remaining batter.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until golden. Let stand 5 minutes before removing muffins from tin.
Sift a little confectioners sugar over muffins just before serving if you like.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Mix rice, onion soup mix and celery soup with 1 can of water. Cook to rice directions.
When chicken is cooked, place on cooked rice mixture.
Salt and pepper chicken.
Lay in baking pan; spread mushroom soup on chicken.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours (cover last hour).
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and marshmallow whip; spread on platter. Cover with caramel topping and nuts. Dip apples in and enjoy.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring until thick. Add the vanilla.
Makes 3 to 4 cups.

title: pea soup
directions: In large, heavy pot, cook celery, carrots and onion in olive oil until crisp-tender.
Stir in water, peas, salt, thyme and pepper.
Bring to boiling, then reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, 45 to 60 minutes or until peas are tender.
Add parsley.
Simmer, uncovered, for 45 to 60 minutes or until thick.
If desired, place 1/2 cup cooked brown rice atop individual servings.
Makes 8 (1 cup) servings.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pan. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer for about 25 minutes. For better stew, place in crock pot for about 2 to 3 hours. Stir when needed.

title: iron skillet chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa in bowl.
Mix egg yolks and milk in another bowl.

title: turkey flautas
directions: Brown turkey, onion and pepper in 1 tablespoon shortening. Add broth and cornstarch.
Cook until thick.
Place 1 heaping tablespoon of mixture on tortilla.
Roll up and stick with toothpick.
Toothpick will keep them from unrolling while deep frying.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Serve with picante sauce and sour cream.

title: banana-nut cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients; blend with shortening, one-half of the sour cream and bananas.
Mix until flour is damp; beat at low speed for 2 minutes.
Add remaining sour cream, flavoring, eggs and nuts.
Pour into 8-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 35 to 50 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: asparagus mold
directions: Heat soup to boiling; remove from fire and add lemon flavored gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cheese and stir until melted and mixed.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Turn into mold and chill.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, combine pumpkin, butter and spices.
Mix well.
In small bowl, beat eggs until frothy. Add sugars, flour, salt and milk.
Mix well.
Pour into pumpkin mixture.
Mix well.

title: blueberry lemon muffins
directions: Make well and add oil, milk and 1 well beaten egg; stir in dry ingredients until moist.
Toss in sugared blueberries.
Add lemon peel and combine.
Put in muffin pans or bread pan for a loaf. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
These are better yet after being dipped in hot melted butter and sugar.

title: rye bread spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Cut out center of round loaf of rye bread to form bowl.
Fill emptied round rye with chilled dip.
Cut up removed bread to dip with.

title: hunter's breakfast
directions: Add in order to a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let set overnight in fridge.
Cook at 350° for 40 minutes to an hour.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Cut cake slices into 3 pieces each and set aside.
Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water in large bowl.
Prepare pudding, using package directions.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook in pan until thick; pour in baked pie shell.
Add meringue to top and brown.

title: butterscotch banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Set aside.
In large bowl, combine bananas, sugar, eggs and butter.
Beat until creamy.
Gradually add flour mixture alternately with milk; mix until well blended.
Stir in 2 cups chopped nuts and butterscotch flavored morsels.
Pour batter equally into 2 well-greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Sprinkle tops equally with remaining 2/3 cup chopped nuts.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; stir well.
Beat egg and add yeast mixture, sugar, oleo and flour.
Mix well.
Use immediately or refrigerate in airtight container.
Will keep for up to 2 weeks.
Spoon batter in well greased muffin tin.
Fill 1/2 full. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken delight
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Place chicken in baking pan. Pour mixture over the chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° until chicken is tender.

title: baked cheese appetizer
directions: Roll out dough; pinch seams together.
Place cheese in center; cover cheese with dough (wrapping around all the cheese).
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Let set, then cut into wedges.
Can be served with salsa or mustard as a spread.

title: mini pecan pies
directions: Mix and chill for 1 hour.
Roll into 24 balls and press into mini muffin tins.
Add filling.

title: turkey legs and beans
directions: Place washed turkey legs in a pot with enough water to cover them; add celery and onion, then cook until meat is done.
Remove meat and add the beans to cook while you are deboning the meat. Discard the bones and skin.
Put meat back into the pot.
Mix well and season to taste with garlic and sugar.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and Crisco.
Add warm water, vinegar and salt.
Work all together real well.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie crust.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets until fork tender.
Cool, peel and then slice into a large bowl.
Stir in sour cream, onions, 1 cup cheese, salt and pepper.
Turn mixture into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika. Cover.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: buttermilk pecan pie
directions: Beat together butter, sugar and eggs, one at a time.
Blend in flour, lemon juice and vanilla.
Stir in buttermilk and pecans. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes or until set. Cool on wire rack.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 8 servings.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, raisins, half the milk, sugar, vanilla, lemon peel and salt in a large mixing bowl.
In a smaller bowl, beat together remaining milk, eggs and spices.
Blend milk mixture into rice mixture.
Pour into a buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: pastry for a double-crust pie
directions: Combine flour and salt in a large bowl. Cut in shortening with pastry blender or large blending fork.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon water over part of mixture; gently toss with a fork.
Push to side of bowl.
Repeat until all is moistened.
Form dough into 2 balls if rolling a double crust.

title: pumpkin-glazed pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and pumpkin until light and fluffy.
Stir in vanilla.
Measure flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, allspice and ginger and mix in bowl.
Stir into creamed mixture to make a rather soft cookie dough.
Stir in nuts. Spoon out onto greased cookie sheets about 2 inches apart in rounded teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove while hot onto rack.
Cool slightly.
Spoon glaze over while cookies are still warm.

title: old fashion sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Slowly add dry ingredients that have been sifted together.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in hot oven (400°) for 7 minutes or until slightly brown.
Do not overbake!
Makes 5 dozen.

title: pumpkin-nut muffins
directions: Grease 12 (3-inch) muffin pan cups (or spray with Pam).
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and all spices onto wax paper.
Beat together eggs, buttermilk, melted butter, vanilla, sugar and pumpkin in a large bowl.
Stir in dry ingredients all at once just until moistened.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Spoon into prepared muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Remove from cups and cool on wire rack.
Makes large, high muffins.

title: chess pie
directions: Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: cranapple butter
directions: In medium saucepan, combine applesauce and cranberry sauce. Cook over medium heat until cranberry sauce melts.
Add margarine and spices and blend well.
Cool slightly.
Pour into clean jars or non-metal containers.
Cover with tight fitting lids.
Store in refrigerator up to 3 weeks.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: citric acid punch(golden punch)
directions: Mix cold water and sugar.
Mix hot water and citric acid. Combine all ingredients except ginger ale.
Freeze.
Thaw until mushy; add ginger ale.
Serves 150.

title: sea mist
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; chill.
Just before serving, stir in ginger ale.

title: quick baked apple pies
directions: Roll biscuits out flat, then put cooked apples into each one. Close them together and press them around the edges with fork. Place them on a buttered pan.
Place in oven.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 8 to 16 pies.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time. Then add flour and extract and fold in 7-Up.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: lo-cal egg nog
directions: Beat egg whites at high speed until they form soft peaks.
In a large bowl with same beaters and high speed, beat yolks and sugar substitute until lemon colored.
Stir in milk, rum, vanilla and nutmeg.
With wire whisk, fold beaten egg whites into milk mixture. To serve, sprinkle with additional nutmeg.
Serve immediately. Makes 5 (1 cup) servings.

title: layer salad
directions: Put lettuce pieces on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Lay sliced eggs on top of this.
Add minced onion on top of this.
Put layer of chopped green pepper.
Put layer of chopped celery.
Put layer of uncooked peas.

title: baked apples supreme
directions: Pare and core apples.
Slice each apple horizontally into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Mix the sugars, chopped pecans and cinnamon together.
Take 1/4 cup of this mixture and add raisins to it.
Set aside.
Roll out dough 1/8-inch thick and cut into four 7 x 7-inch squares.
Dip apple slices into beaten egg, then into sugar and nut mixture, coating each side.
In center of (1) pastry square, stack (only) four coated apple slices.
Stuff core with raisin, sugar, nut mixture.
Wet 4 edges of dough with water and bring up corners, pinching edges of dough together to form a 4 cornered shape.
Continue with 3 remaining pastry squares.
Leave top open by folding back the dough slightly.
Place 1 tablespoon butter on top of each apple.
Brush edges with milk and sprinkle with remaining sugar and cinnamon.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 40 minutes or until apples test done and pastry golden brown.
Pipe fresh whipped cream around base and serve warm.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: apple muffins
directions: In small bowl, combine buttermilk, bran flakes and baking soda; set aside.
In mixer bowl, beat together prune puree, egg whites, sweetener and molasses.
Stir in buttermilk mixture, flour and grated apple.
Blend thoroughly.
Spoon into muffin tins lined with baking cups or coated with nonstick spray.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.
Makes 12 muffins.
One muffin equals 105 calories, 0 calories from fat, 0 total fat and 1 mg cholesterol.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Note:
Use fruits listed or fruit of your choice.

title: never fall meringue
directions: Blend cornstarch and cold water in a saucepan. Add boiling water and cook, stirring, until clear and thickened. Let stand until completely cold. With electric beater at high speed, beat egg whites until foamy. Gradually add sugar and beat until stiff, but not dry. Turn mixer to low speed and add salt and vanilla. Gradually beat in cold cornstarch mixture. Turn mixer again to high speed and beat well. Spread meringue over cooled pie filling. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes. This meringue cuts beautifully and never gets sticky.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Remove and discard skin from chicken. Boil chicken in water (salted or unsalted, as you prefer) until done.
Remove chicken, reserving broth.
Debone and cut up chicken; set aside.
Cook spaghetti in reserved chicken broth; do not drain (spaghetti will soak up broth).
Add cheese to spaghetti.
Cook bell pepper and onion in oleo until tender; add to spaghetti along with Ro-Tel tomatoes, peas and chicken.
Mix well and spoon into casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes on low heat (275° to 325°, depending upon oven).

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat cream cheese, then add cocktail sauce or seafood sauce. Beat in the chopped shrimp and add Worcestershire.

title: schaefer's wafers(from gov. wm. donald schaefer)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/3 cup sugar and beat 3 minutes.
Add another 1/3 cup of sugar and beat 3 minutes more.
Add vanilla.
Fold in chocolate chips.

title: date torte
directions: Boil until thick the dates, butter and water; cool, then add soda, sugar, eggs, salt, vanilla, flour and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
When cool, whip 1 pint of whipping cream and dribble with chocolate syrup.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: petite quiches
directions: Combine cream cheese, oleo and flour in a mixing bowl.
Blend well.
Shape into roll about 2 inches wide and 8 inches long. Wrap in plastic wrap and chill well or freeze.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls (24).
Place in ungreased miniature muffin tins. Press dough against bottom and sides of pans.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil and boil for 30 seconds.
Remove from heat. Add the peanut butter and stir.
Add the oatmeal. Spoon on wax paper.

title: pork chops italian
directions: Combine Parmesan cheese and breadcrumbs in a shallow dish. Dredge pork chops in mixture. Brown chops in hot oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Place chops in a lightly greased 11 x 7-inch baking dish. Pour spaghetti sauce over chops. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and bake 5 minutes. Serve over hot cooked fettucine.

title: fried squash bread
directions: Wash, clean and dice 2 summer squash.
Cook until soft (do not cook dry), leave about 3/4 cup of water in pot.
Combine corn meal, egg and buttermilk.
Add squash and water; mix together. Fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: squash pie
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
Pour in uncooked pie crust. Cook at
350° for 30 minutes or until knife stuck into center comes out clean.

title: zucchini-chip omelet
directions: About 30 minutes before serving:

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs; cool.
Cut in half after removing shells.
Remove yellow part of egg.
Mash with remaining ingredients.
Fill the whites with this mixture.

title: no work meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
If the zucchini is large, remove the seeds before grating.
Then add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla to the eggs.
Mix lightly, but well.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased and wax paper lined loaf pans.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: christmas salad
directions: Stir sugar into the cranberries and set aside.
Prepare strawberry jello according to directions, when it begins to thicken, add fruit, nuts and celery.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: german apple cake
directions: Beat together eggs, oil, sugar, salt, flour, vanilla, cinnamon and soda.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: cherry burst pie
directions: In a medium bowl, combine condensed milk, lemon juice and vanilla. Mix until well blended. Fold in remaining ingredients, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Mound mixture into crust.
Freeze until firm, 2 to 3 hours.
Let stand for 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.

title: cheesy squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in small amount of boiling water for 10 to 12 minutes, until very tender; drain.
Set aside.

title: turkey or chicken dressing
directions: Mix cornmeal, milk, oil and egg and pour into greased pan. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Cool and crumble into large pan. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Pour into large pan and bake at 450° until brown.

title: my favorite stuffing
directions: Brown sausage.
Melt butter and cook onion.
Mix all together.

title: dirty rice
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and cook in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: mayfield lemon pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar, add boiling water.
Stir and cook until no taste of raw starch.
Beat egg yolks and add slowly to first mixture, cook over low heat until egg is cooked.
Add butter, lemon juice and rind, cool.
Add to baked pie shell and cover with meringue (be sure meringue touches all around the crust).

title: tex-mex lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, over medium-high heat, brown beef with the onion and drain the liquid.
Add the tomato paste, picante sauce, water, oregano and basil.
Mix well and set aside.
Combine Ricotta or cottage cheese and 3/4 cup Mozzarella cheese in a large bowl; set aside.
Spray an 8 x 11-inch baking pan with nonstick vegetable spray.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Soak poppy seed in water for 1 hour.
Place cake mix in a bowl.
Add poppy seed, eggs and remaining water.
Beat 3 minutes. Pour into greased and floured layer pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Split layers and frost with raspberry jam.

title: spinach dip
directions: Green onions and water chestnuts can be chopped together in food processor.

title: classic lasagna
directions: In large skillet, brown beef with onion and garlic. Drain and stir in tomato juice, mushrooms, tomato paste, Worcestershire sauce, oregano, salt and pepper.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer 1/2 of noodles, 1/2 of sauce, 1/2 of cottage cheese, 1/2 of Parmesan and 1/2 of Mozzarella.
Repeat all layers.
Cover with foil and let rest at least 1 hour (best if left in refrigerator overnight).

title: cold cucumber soup *
directions: Place garlic, dill and half of yogurt in blender; puree for 10 seconds.
Add cucumbers and blend until cucumbers are still visible.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Fold in rest of yogurt and serve.
Serves 4.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix together sugar, flour, baking powder and peach juice.
Pour on top of oleo and place peaches on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: slo-cook beef
directions: Slice meat cross grain; may brown in oil (optional).
Place meat in slo-cooker (crock-pot).
In blender or processor, place all other ingredients; process until onion is minced.
Pour over meat strips.
Slo-cook for 5 to 6 hours.
Stir midway through, if possible.
Makes 5 generous servings.

title: stuffed hawaiian bread
directions: Mix mixture together and chill both it and the bread separately for 2 hours.
Cut bread into thirds; layer mixture in it.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Cut into thin slices before serving.

title: tuna boats
directions: Prepare tuna mixture (tuna, salad cubes, mayonnaise, egg and onion).
Set aside.
Slice cucumbers lengthwise and scoop out pulp. Slice small length off bottom so cucumber will sit flat.
Scoop tuna into "boats;" sprinkle with paprika.
Chill and serve.

title: cherry nut bread
directions: Mix all together with juice from 1 quart canned cherries. Bake in greased, floured loaf pans for 1 hour.

title: korean chicken
directions: Blend ingredients in blender.
Take chicken drummettes and fry until done.
Then dip in sauce.
Serve immediately.

title: the cake that doesn't last
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in center; add eggs, vegetable oil, vanilla, mashed bananas and pineapple.
Stir, do not beat!
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 75 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes, turn out of pan.
Glaze when cool.

title: tortillas de harina
directions: Mix flour, salt, baking soda and lard together with hands, gradually adding water as you mix until ingredients are damp. Knead dough about 5 minutes.
Cover; let stand for 10 to 20 minutes.
Shape dough into balls.
Preheat ungreased heavy skillet or comal until very hot.
Roll out each dough ball to form a circle.
Cook about 30 seconds on each side.
Tortillas should be soft and pliable.
Stack and cover tortillas to keep warm.

title: no bake stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half lengthwise.
Remove and discard stem ends and seeds.
Parboil in boiling salted water for 10 minutes; drain. Add sugar and basil to tomato sauce and set aside.
Brown ground beef and onion well in a large skillet.
Stir in 1/2 cup of tomato sauce mixture, 1/4 cup of rice and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Pour melted margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs over evenly.
Sprinkle chopped nuts evenly, then chocolate (or other) chips followed by coconut.
Pour condensed milk over all. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes before cutting.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables or crackers.

title: fish cakes
directions: Grind soyameat.
Add all other ingredients.
Form into patties and roll in bread crumbs *.
Fry in oil in skillet and bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350° to finish cooking.

title: apple butter
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in 250° oven for 2 hours, or cook in a crock-pot 24 hours on low heat.

title: best ever brownies
directions: Melt chocolate with butter.
(Microwave 2 minutes on High power.)
Beat eggs well in bowl.
Gradually add sugar until mixture is fluffy-thick (about 10 minutes).
Stir in vanilla and chocolate mixture, then fold in flour, salt and walnuts.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until shiny and firm on top.
Cool completely, then cut into 24 (2-inch) squares.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in greased 7 x 11-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° until it is thick and starts to brown.

title: simplified chicken kiev
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients, except Shake 'n Bake and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle Shake 'n Bake over the top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large nonstick skillet brown beef, stirring occasionally.
Remove beef; discard all but 1 teaspoon drippings.
Add onion and saute until soft.
Add garlic and continue cooking for 1 minute.

title: fruit salad
directions: Melt marshmallows and crushed pineapple in a double boiler. Chill until thick.
Add whipped cream, fruit cocktail, bananas and coconut to the chilled mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: fluffy pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, spices and the vanilla pudding (dry). Add this mixture to whipped cream and beat 1 minute.
Pour into 9-inch baked pie shell and chill.
You can substitute 1 package of the imitation whipped cream for the real whipped cream (or Cool Whip).
Put a spoonful of whipping cream on top when serving.

title: christmas cranberry bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar and baking powder in a large bowl. Combine eggs, milk, melted butter and vanilla in a medium bowl. Make a well in the dry ingredients.
Add egg mixture, stirring just till moistened.
Fold in cranberries and walnuts.
Spread in a greased 9 x 5 x 3 in loaf pan.
Bake in 350 oven 55 minutes or till toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan or wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove loaf from pan.
Cook thoroughly on wire rack.
Wrap and store overnight for easier slicing.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: quiche unique
directions: Combine cheeses, pepperoni and onion.
Sprinkle in pie shell. Combine eggs, half and half, salt and oregano.
Pour over cheeses. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Allow to stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Garnish with parsley.
Place on cookie sheet to bake.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Combine ingredients. Place in greased casserole, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: mint dressing for fruit
directions: Combine mandarin juice, sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Stir until smooth, heating to a boil.
Remove from heat, stir constantly, stir in beaten egg, return to low heat and cook a minute or two longer, stirring briskly.
Remove from heat and blend in mandarin peel and lemon juice.
Cool, then stir in sour cream and mint.
Serve over fresh fruit or with fruit gelatin salads.
Makes 1 cup.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift the first five ingredients into a large bowl.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Add egg and orange juice.
Fold in raisins and cranberries.
Stir only until mixed - should still be lumpy. Spoon into greased 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pan.
Bake 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: salmon dip
directions: Blend; chill and serve.

title: w w salad
directions: Mix all together and let stand 1 hour.

title: helen's ham loaf
directions: Mix together well. Pour all over loaf. Bake another 1/2 hour.

title: louisiana casserole
directions: Cook onion, green pepper and garlic in butter until tender-crisp.
Add crawfish or shrimp; continue cooking 3 minutes. Stir in soup, rice, parsley, lemon juice and seasonings.
Add bread after soaking in milk.
Mix well.
Spoon into buttered shallow 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: choc-cherry cake
directions: Combine all by hand.
Pour into a 10 x 15-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until done.

title: chili with beans
directions: Fry hamburger and onion together until hamburger is browned. Break up hamburger while frying to eliminate large chunks.
Drain grease.
Add tomatoes, pepper and seasoning.
Cook 1 hour.
Add beans.
Cook 15 minutes more. Serve with crackers.
Makes 6 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in top of boiler. Remove from heat. Add sugar and eggs. Beat well. Add flour, salt and baking powder. Beat well. Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into buttered pan. Bake for 27 minutes at 325° in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Be sure and do not cook too long.
A little gooey is alright.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Do not mix the ingredients. In a 9 x 13 casserole dish, layer ingredients in the order given.

title: florentine stuffed turkey breast half
directions: Rub turkey breast with 1 tablespoon margarine, thyme and garlic.
In large, nonstick skillet, over medium-high heat, saute onion and celery in one tablespoon margarine for 4 to 5 minutes or until soft.
Fold in spinach, broth, bread, walnuts, apple, salt, nutmeg and pepper until mixture is well combined.

title: hot corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Bake approximately 25 minutes in a 425° oven.

title: orange slice bar
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add rest of ingredients to butter and stir well.
Spread in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden.
May sprinkle with powdered sugar but is not necessary.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: florida white fruit cake
directions: Cream until light and fluffy, butter and sugar.
Add one at a time eggs beaten well after each.
Sift flour, Combine in a large bowl fruit and pecans.
Thoroughly blend sifted flour with fruit and nuts.
Add sugar mixture and extracts, mix thoroughly and spoon into a tube pan that has been greased well.
Place into a cold oven and bake for 2 1/2 hours at 250 degrees.

title: linguine with no-cook tomato sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients, but linguine, in a large serving bowl. Let stand for flavors to blend.

title: baked corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in a 9 x 12 x 2-inch dish.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: favorite cappuccino
directions: Place hot chocolate in a coffee mug.
Stir in coffee to mix. Use about 2/3 cup coffee.
Pour in one shot of brandy and top with whipped cream.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat together first 3 ingredients.
Sift together and add next 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased tube pan or Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: edible play dough(peanut butter)
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and first blend with a spoon, then with hands.
Shape into balls, snakes, pizzas or whatever. Makes enough for 10 kids.

title: prize winning chili 1981
directions: Brown hamburger and chorizo; salt to taste.
Add everything else.
Keep tasting!

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Spoon pie filling into a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Spoon pineapple over pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over pineapple.
Drizzle butter of cake mix.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 22 minutes.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Sift sugar, salt and baking powder with flour in bowl.
Add potatoes, shortening and milk.
Make a soft dough.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until firm.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Mix together and divide batter in half. To first half, add 1 cup chopped nuts and bake in 3 layers. To second half, add 1 teaspoon each cloves, spice and cinnamon and 1 pound ground raisins. Bake in 3 layers.

title: crisp fried onion rings
directions: Peel onions; cut into 1/2-inch thick slices and separate into rings.
Place in a bowl; add cold water to cover.
Chill for 1 hour.
Drain on paper towels.
Combine flour and next 4 ingredients; stir well.
Add beer and egg, stirring with a wire whisk until smooth.
Pour oil to depth of 3 inches in Dutch oven. Heat to 375°.
Dip onion rings into batter; fry, a few at a time, for 3 minutes or until golden.
Drain on paper towels.
Yields 6 servings.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Core cabbage and steam in hot water for 5 minutes, or until leaves come off easily.
Combine all other ingredients with rice.
Place about 1/4 cup of mixture on each cabbage leaf.
Roll up leaf; turn edges under.
Secure by rolling as tightly as possible.
Cover with reserved liquid from cabbage and tomatoes.
Cook in saucepan for about 45 minutes, until rice and beef are done.

title: rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour in greased muffin pan. Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cracker pudding
directions: Heat milk until very hot.
Mix 2 egg yolks, 1/2 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Stir together until a smooth paste forms.
Add the paste mixture to the hot milk and cook well.
Add crushed saltine crackers, coconut (if desired) and vanilla.
Stir well.
Put mixture into 1-quart baking dish.
Beat 2 egg whites and 4 tablespoons sugar until stiff peaks form.
Put on top of custard and bake in 400° oven until light brown.

title: fast apple pie
directions: Melt butter; add flour, sugar and cinnamon to make a paste. Pour half in crust.
Add apples and pour remaining paste over apples and add top crust.
Bake in oven at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer in baking dish the ingredients in the same order.
Mix soup and sour cream together and pour over ingredients, then sprinkle Parmesan cheese on the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: corned beef stew
directions: Cook potatoes and onions in 6 to 7 cups of water until done (soft).
Break up corned beef into potato and onion and add instant rice.
Last, add carrot coins.
Salt and pepper to taste. Serve hot with biscuits.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix together and make small balls.
Place in an 8 x 10-inch pan.

title: braised beef with cabbage
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add beef.
Brown on all sides and remove.
Add onions to skillet.
Cook slowly until brown.
Add browned beef.
Stir in 1 cup of water.
Add apple and tomatoes. Sprinkle sugar, salt and pepper.
Bring to boiling, reduce heat and simmer covered 2 hrs.
Add potatoes and cabbage to meat mixture; simmer, covered, 20 minutes longer, or until vegetables are tender. Serves 4.

title: one cup salad
directions: Mix and let stand several hours.
Can add a sliced banana just before serving.

title: helen's cheesecake
directions: Crust:
Prepare pie crust as directed on package directions using a spring-form pan.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in greased loaf pans. Makes 2 loaves.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and then flour and cinnamon. Add oats and mix good.
Bake at 275° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Bake in a large pan and serve in pan.

title: pepper steak stir-fry
directions: In a large skillet, stir-fry garlic in 1 tablespoon butter for 1 minute.
Add onions and green peppers; stir-fry for about 4 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Transfer vegetables with a slotted spoon to a bowl.
Add remaining butter or margarine to skillet; stir-fry meat (1/2 at a time) until the meat is cooked through (2 to 3 minutes).
Return all the steak and vegetables to the skillet.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, reserving 1/4 of the potato chips. Pour into greased baking dish.
Top with remaining potato chips.
Bake for 15 minutes at 450°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pizza fondue
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off fat.
Add pizza sauce, cheeses and beef into saucepan or fondue pot.
Cook on medium heat until cheese is melted.
Cut up French bread into cubes and use to dip into fondue.

title: ronnie's chocolate chunk cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine.
Press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake pie crust (9-inch) for 5 to 7 minutes or until very light golden.
Remove from oven and let cool. Reduce oven temperature to 325°.
Meanwhile, cut candy bars into small pieces.
Place on bottom of pie crust.
In small bowl combine sugar and cream cheese, beat until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add the sour cream and peanut butter, beating until mixture is smooth.
Pour mixture over candy bars.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until center is set.
Cool completely.
When cool, heat heavy cream until warm, add chocolate chips and remove from heat.
Stir until smooth, then pour over top of cooled pie.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Keep in fridge.

title: sloppy jane sandwiches
directions: In slow cooker, combine frankfurters with beans, mustard, onion and chili sauce.
Cover and cook on low for 2 to 3 hours. Spoon over toasted frankfurter buns.

title: swiss steak
directions: Trim off fat and cut steak in serving size pieces.
Place steak in pot.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over it.
Lay on mushrooms, celery and green peppers.
Add Worcestershire sauce, then tomatoes, garlic and black pepper.
Cover and simmer for about 1 1/2 hours, until fork-tender, stirring several times to mix flavors.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine cooking oil, sugar, cinnamon, vanilla and salt and blend well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and crushed pineapple (undrained), blending well.
Fold in carrots, coconut, raisins and nuts.
Blend well.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) round cake pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Combine pudding mix and buttermilk.
Beat until well blended. Add mandarin oranges and pineapple tidbits (both well drained). Fold in Cool Whip.
Break fudge striped cookies into pieces about the size of a dime and add to other ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate.
Keeps well.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Cook eggs, sugar and pineapple juice as custard.
Stir in fruit when custard is cooled.
Add whipped cream carefully.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in large, heavy skillet.
Blend in flour.
Cook over low heat until bubbly, stirring constantly.
Gradually add broth and milk to flour mixture.
Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add chicken, peas and carrots, seasonings and egg.
Heat well.
Spoon into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with flaky pastry.
Turn pastry edges under and press firmly to rim of dish.
Cut slits in pastry.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix together.
Put in greased 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: myrtle's punch
directions: Put the sugar in 1/2 gallon water and heat until sugar is dissolved.
Add other ingredients.
Chill.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all together.
Can be stored in refrigerator about 6 weeks.
Grease muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: infallible rice
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Combine rice and hot broth.
Bring to a boil on top of stove.
Cover and place in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: crock-pot peanut clusters
directions: Put in crock-pot on the lowest temperature.
Cover and cook 1 hour.
Stir well and re-cover.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Re-cover each time for full cooking time of 2 hours.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper and cool.
Makes about 100
pieces.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter or margarine.
Add soups and Cheez Whiz.
Cook rice and broccoli separately.
Add rice and broccoli to soup mixture.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Mix together the margarine, flour and nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: cream cheese and dried beef ball
directions: Combine ingredients; save 1/4 of the beef.
Shape into 1 or 2 balls.
Roll in saved beef.
Wrap in plastic and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon in large bowl. Add eggs and oil.
Stir (don't beat).
Stir in pineapple, pecans, bananas and vanilla.
Put batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove and cool.
Spread frosting between layers and on top.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup nuts over frosting on top.

title: christmas refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour and soda, which have been sifted together. Add vanilla, dates, raisins, nuts, candied pineapple and cherries. Mix together well and shape into rolls. Put rolls to chill in refrigerator several hours. Slice and bake or put rolls in freezer and slice and bake as needed. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: morning muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease bottom of regular size muffin pan.
Beat egg; stir in milk and oil.
Mix in remaining ingredients except jelly or jam.
Mix until flour is moist. Batter should be lumpy.
Fill muffin cups 1/2 full; drop 1 teaspoon jelly or jam in center of each, add batter to fill cups 2/3 full.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from pan immediately.

title: hot crabbies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: grandma's west virginia buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients except shortening.
(Melt shortening in pan in oven.)
Roll dough with fingers or rolling pin to about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut biscuits.
Coat both sides of biscuits with melted shortening, then bake for 15 minutes at 400°.

title: beef and broccoli
directions: Slice beef into very thin strips.
In cup, mix cornstarch, broth, soy sauce and pepper until smooth.
Set aside.

title: shuckbread(or buhaha)
directions: Mix dry ingredients, add water until mixture is stiff enough to handle easily.
Form into balls about the size of a tennis ball.
Wrap each ball in a corn shuck that has been boiled for 10 minutes in water.

title: ranch burgers
directions: Mix salad dressing in with ground beef and pat into 4 patties. Grill or broil until done.

title: fried onion rings
directions: Cut onions into 1/2 slices. Separate into rings.

title: coconut kisses
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Add enough milk to fill freezer. Freeze as usual in freezer.

title: parmesan meatballs
directions: Roll into 1-inch balls.
Broil. Place over cooked egg noodles to serve.
Can make sauce to pour over top.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion.
Put in buttered casserole.
Put in frozen broccoli; cover with cheese, rice and soup.
Bake at 350° for 2 minutes uncovered.
Stir and cover; bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: delightful green beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Beat egg slightly in saucepan.
Add sugar, vinegar and grease.
Heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Heat beans thoroughly.
Pour sauce over beans.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.

title: venison stew with beer and onions
directions: Sprinkle meat with venison seasoning.
This can be purchased at Pineville Sport and Tackle.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Melt butter in heavy skillet or Dutch oven.
Saute onions and then remove.
Brown meat in saucepan and remove.
Add flour to pan and cook until browned.
Add beer and bring to a boil.
Return meat and onions to pan.
Cover and simmer gently for 1 1/2 hours or until tender. Excellent served over noodles.

title: chicken scallops with mustard glaze
directions: Mix flour, marjoram, thyme and pepper; put aside 1 tablespoon. Rub mixture on chicken.
Spray pan with Pam.
Add butter; melt. Cook chicken until brown (about 2 minutes per side).
Take out chicken and set aside.
Add vermouth to pan; boil until glazed (about 5 minutes).
Mix in chicken broth, mustard and lemon peel; boil 2 minutes.
Mix cream into reserved seasoned flour.
Whisk in 1/4 cup of broth and add to pan.
Simmer until thickened and smooth, stirring constantly (about 3 minutes).
Return chicken to skillet.
Adjust heat so sauce is just shaking and cook until opaque (about 2 minutes per side).
Transfer to plates.
Garnish with lemon slices and watercress.
Takes about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and cook 2 minutes after mixture comes to a boil, then add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Mix and drop by spoonful onto wax paper.

title: turkish salad
directions: Peel cucumbers. Slice lengthwise and discard seeds. Peel and seed tomatoes; dice. Put in bowl and cover with salt. Mix well. Chill for 1 hour. Chop dill. Combine remaining ingredients. Add and mix gently. Chill, covered, 2 hours. Drain liquid before serving.

title: garden macaroni salad
directions: Combine ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute bell pepper and onion in margarine in saucepan.
Add soup (undiluted), rice, broccoli and cheese; pour in baking dish and bake for about 20 minutes.

title: baked corn pudding
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 225° for 4 hours.

title: bounty rice
directions: Saute beef, onion and green pepper until meat is browned; drain. Stir in tomatoes, seasonings, rice and cabbage.
Cover and cook for 10 to 15 minutes or until cabbage is tender. Stir in sour cream. Sprinkle cheese over top of rice/meat mixture and allow cheese to melt, about 2 to 3 minutes.

title: chili con carne
directions: Combine first two ingredients in a Dutch oven or a large saucepan.
Brown meat; drain off fat.
Add next 12 ingredients; stir to blend.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lettuce and pea salad
directions: Layer in bowl, bite size pieces of lettuce.
Add chopped celery, sliced onions and half of peas.
Make another layer in the same order.
Mix mayonnaise and Sweet 'N Low.
Spread over salad and sprinkle with bacon bits and cheese.

title: potato soup
directions: Wash, peel and dice potatoes; dice onion.
Cover potatoes and onions with water in covered saucepan.
Cook for 15 minutes. Drain, keeping 1 1/2 cups of the cooking water.
Mash the vegetables with a potato masher.
Add butter, cooking water, milk, salt and pepper.
Heat; add more water if a thinner soup is desired.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Take your croissant rolls and roll out like pie crust on a pizza pan.
Bake until flaky brown; follow cooking directions on package.
Let cool.

title: no-knead batter bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water in large mixing bowl; add oil, egg, milk, sugar and flour.
Mix well; spoon into greased muffin pan. Bake at 375° until good and brown, about 30 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Combine in a heavy skillet the shortening and ground beef and cook until brown. Add onion and green pepper. Cook over low heat until tender. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Add water if too thick. Add 1 (1 pound 1 ounce) can kidney beans, drained. Simmer for 10 minutes longer. Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: disappearing tarts
directions: Cut pastry dough into squares and place in muffin tins.
Spoon pie filling evenly over dough.
Bake at 400° until pastry is golden brown and filling is bubbling.
Remove tarts from pan ASAP to prevent from becoming soggy.
Serve warm topped with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: herb-baked scallops
directions: Wash and drain scallops.
Place in single layer in dish.
Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle with parsley, basil, salt and pepper. Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 5 minutes.
Stir, then bake for 20 minutes more or until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: white bean and chicken soup(serves 4)
directions: Place in crock-pot and cook on high for 3 hours.

title: nutty peach crisp
directions: Layer* ingredients in order listed in an ungreased oblong 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: no bake pan cookies
directions: Mix sugars, butter, milk and cocoa. Cook for 2 to 3 minutes at a rolling boil (over medium heat).
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Mix well. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a greased pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix green beans, English peas, corn, onion, celery and bell pepper and place in a bowl.
Then mix vinegar, oil, sugar and salt and pour this over the vegetables.
Let marinate in refrigerator for 24 to 48 hours.
Makes approximately 2 quarts or 8 to 10 servings.

title: holiday hot cranberry punch
directions: Combine juices, spices and sugar in a 2-quart microproof dish. Cover and cook on High (maximum power) for 9 to 11 minutes or until mixture boils.
Strain into warmed punch bowl and garnish with clove-studded orange slices.
Yields approximately 20 servings.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut in bars.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: our favorite almost sugar-free cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and mix together well.
Add dry ingredients and blend well.
Stir in nuts, dates and coconut. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased or sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburg and onion in a skillet.
Add tomato paste, tomato juice, salt, pepper and oregano.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Cook lasagna noodles.
Place in a cake pan.
Start with sauce, noodles and then cheeses.
Make 3 layers, ending with Swiss cheese on the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato bake
directions: Mix potatoes, 1/2 cup butter or margarine, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese together in large bowl.
Put into baking dish. Crush up corn flakes; mix with the other 1/2 cup butter or margarine and spread over potato mixture.
Beak at 400° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: thai ribbons
directions: Soak 30 (6-inch) bamboo skewers in water.

title: missy's macaroni surprise
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Add tomato paste, 1/2 cup cheese and seasonings; mix well.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Place in 9-inch pie plate, pressing together to form a crust.
Flute edge.
Fill crust with meat mixture; top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: zucchini squash relish
directions: Grind up zucchini and onion.
Add salt.
Let stand for several hours or overnight.
Drain; rinse with cold water and drain again. Add nutmeg, mustard, sugar, pepper, vinegar, turmeric, celery seed, red and green peppers.
Cook 30 minutes.
Seal hot in hot sterile jars.
Makes 7-8 pints.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry onion and hamburger together.
Cook rice in salt water 4 or 5 minutes or until tender.
Drain off excess water.
Pour rice and tomatoes in skillet and let simmer for about 1/2 hour or put in oven at 325° or 350°; bake until almost dry.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie shells. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat and bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until done.
Serve plain or with vanilla ice cream.

title: sweet 'n sour stir-fry chicken
directions: Boil chicken in water to cover for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool and debone.
Drain pineapple.
Reserve juice.
Heat large deep skillet; add 1/4 cup oil.
Cut all vegetables into small pieces. Stir-fry quickly all except cabbage.
Add chicken; turn to low heat.

title: cherry rhubarb sauce
directions: Place rhubarb in a large saucepan.
Pour sugar over and let stand 1 hour.
Add water to mixture in saucepan.
Bring to a boil slowly, uncovered.
Cook 1 to 5 minutes until rhubarb is soft. Cool.
Cover and refrigerate several hours before serving.
Serves 6.

title: fluffy jello
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 quarts warm water.
When jello starts to thicken, beat with beater and then add remaining ingredients. Chill until firm.

title: untossed salad
directions: Layer in order given.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar and spread over salad; sprinkle cheese over mayonnaise mixture.
Sprinkle Bac*Os over top of cheese.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Combine spaghetti sauce mix, tomato paste, tomato sauce and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Combine eggs, Ricotta or cottage cheese, spinach and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Mix well and set aside. Cook noodles and drain.
Layer noodles, sauce, spinach mixture and Mozzarella cheese.
Top with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: confetti coleslaw parfait
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Stir in cold water and vinegar. Gradually add gelatin to Miracle Whip, mixing until well blended. Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in cabbage, carrots, celery and raisins.
Pour into 1-quart mold. Chill until firm.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cheesy meat pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt butter in skillet; brown beef and onion.
Drain grease; remove from heat.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Spread beef mixture in pie crust.
Spread cheese over beef mixture.
Mix milk, eggs and Worcestershire sauce; pour over meat and cheese.
Set pie pan on cookie sheet.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: southern buttermilk pie
directions: Place rack in lower third of oven; preheat to 400°.
Combine sugar, margarine and flour in medium bowl; beat until smooth and creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in buttermilk, lemon juice and salt.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat and bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes, or until filling sets and is lightly browned.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until bubbly around edges.
Continue cooking 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda until foamy.
Pour over popcorn.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes, in a 200° oven.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Add one cup flour, soda and salt and beat 2 minutes.
Then add alternately the apples, chopped fine and the other 2 cups of flour.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in two loaf pans.
May add one cup of nuts, if desired.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Saute onions and celery in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add carrots, green peppers and then all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes to blend flavors.
Try this; low-fat and very good.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.
Pudding should be golden brown on top.
If not, adjust dish in oven.
It could take up to 1 1/2 hours.

title: mango mousse
directions: Combine mango and sugar in a blender and puree.
In a mixing bowl, stir together cream, lime juice and sour cream.
Meanwhile, soften gelatin in wine over a low heat for 3 minutes or until clear.
Stir gelatin into cream mixture, along with mango puree. Mix well and pour into a ring mold, a glass bowl or 6 parfait glasses.
Chill until firm.
Serves 8.

title: tuna mushroom casserole
directions: In a large saucepan, bring water and bouillon to a boil, stirring to dissolve.
Add the next 8 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Dissolve cornstarch in milk; add to vegetable mixture, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil; boil 2 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in cheese and mayonnaise until cheese is melted.
Fold in noodles and tuna.
Pour into greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Brown bread crumbs in butter; sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender; debone and cut in bite size pieces.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Add chicken soup and sour cream.
Mix together and pour over chicken.
Crush Ritz crackers; add poppy seed.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Melt margarine and pour over top of crackers.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Yum, yum.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Grease with margarine or spray with Pam a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle rice evenly in pan.
Pour margarine and milk over rice. Mix the 2 cans of soup together and spoon over rice.
Lay chicken over rice and soup mixture, then sprinkle onion soup mix over. Seal well with foil and bake 2 hours at 325°.
Do not peek during baking.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes; drain.
Let cool enough to melt butter.
Stir in all ingredients, reserving a small amount of cheese for garnishing.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in small amount of boiling water until tender; drain and mash.
Add salt and pepper.
Combine and add soup, pimiento, carrots, onion, sour cream and 1/2 of breadcrumb mixture.
Put into 2-quart greased casserole dish; put rest of breadcrumb mixture on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 2 hours or until done.

title: annies oyster stew
directions: Cook oysters in small pan with small lump butter.
Cook until the ends
begin
to
curl;	set
aside.
In large pot or saucepan; add
both milk and butter.
Bring to boiling point. Add oysters, heat again if they have cooled too much.
Parsley may be added if desired, salt and pepper to taste.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender. Blend until smooth. Pour into greased and floured pie tin. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: In mixing bowl, beat together ingredients.
Pour in an 8 x 8-inch buttered baking dish.

title: crispy rice marshmallow squares
directions: Butter 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In 3-quart saucepan over low heat, melt margarine.
Add marshmallows, stirring constantly until melted.
Remove from heat.
Quickly add cereal, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated.
Press into prepared pan with back of buttered spoon.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: spicy fish
directions: Rinse fillets and cut into serving size portions.
Heat oil in skillet and sear fish on both sides.
Add picante sauce and simmer fish for 5 to 7 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown ground beef. Drain well. Add salsa and Cheez Whiz. Stir well and place in crock-pot on low.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Combine all ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve topped with crushed taco chips, grated cheese and sour cream.

title: good dry black-eyed peas
directions: Cook the black-eyed peas until almost done. Add hamburger meat or sausage, chopped onion and chopped bell pepper according to taste. Simmer until onion and peppers are tender.

title: (ripe) tomato relish
directions: Peel tomatoes.
Run with peppers, onions and hot peppers through blender.
Tie allspice, cinnamon, celery seed, mustard seed and turmeric in cloth and cook all ingredients 3 to 4 hours or until desired thickness.
Try it; you will like it!

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix everything in bowl except nuts.
Microwave at Medium until chips are melted, 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir once or twice.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into well-greased dish (8 x 8-inches).
Refrigerate until set.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta. While pasta is boiling, cut vegetables. Take 1 pack of dry dressing and pour into bottle of dressing. Shake well and pour over pasta and mix. Then add the other pack of dry dressing on pasta and mix again. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil zucchini until tender.
Saute carrots and onions in 1/2 stick margarine.
Add 1/2 cup croutons, sour cream and soup.
Add squash.
Saute rest of croutons in 1/2 stick margarine.
Top mixture with croutons.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin ice cream roll
directions: In a small bowl, combine flour, pumpkin pie spice, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs at high speed for 5 minutes until pale yellow.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin.
Fold in dry ingredients.
Line a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with greased and floured wax paper.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: stuffed vidalia onions
directions: Peel and core onion.
Retain centers and chop well.
Mix ground beef, 1/2 cup chopped onion, bread crumbs, rice and bell pepper.
Season to taste.
Mix well.
Form mixture into small meat balls and fill each onion shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
If desired, just before serving, add on a slice of Mozzarella cheese to each onion and heat until melted.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Pour bourbon over chopped nuts; toss to coat.
Blend well at room temperature the butter, powdered sugar and evaporated milk. Knead.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Chill firmly and have cool for dipping.

title: ma-mom sutton's coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425°.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add water and cook over low heat until it looks clear.
Add jello and strawberries and pour into pie shell.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.
Top with Cool Whip if desired.

title: tuna patties
directions: Combine egg, tuna, tuna liquid, mustard, half the crumbs and relish in a bowl; mix well.
Shape into 4 patties.
Coat with remaining crumbs; fry in hot shortening for several minutes on each side until browned.
Serve on buns.

title: sweet pea salad
directions: In a medium size bowl, mix all ingredients together. Cover and refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours before serving.
For best results, refrigerate overnight.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: In a 6-quart ice cream freezer, place all ingredients except milk; mix well.
Add the milk to the fill line on container in ice cream freezer.
Prepare ice cream freezer as usual.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: polish dill pickles
directions: Add large sprig of dill, 2 sliced garlic toes and cucumbers to bottom of clean jars.
Bring vinegar, water, salt and alum to boil.
Pour into jars.
Add lids immediately.
They will seal without processing.
Makes 7 quarts.

title: orange delight
directions: Drain oranges, measuring syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add measured liquid. Add sherbet by spoonfuls, stirring until well melted.
Chill until thick.
Fold oranges in.
Chill overnight.
Very refreshing. Children love to help make this.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and drain vegetables.
Cut into desired bite-size pieces. Add broken pieces of bacon and raisins.
Mix Miracle Whip, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over vegetables and toss lightly.

title: cinder cake
directions: Crush cookies in plastic bag with rolling pin or use food processor.
Mix crushed cookies with melted butter.
Measure 3/4 cup and set aside.
Press remaining cookie mixture evenly into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan to form bottom layer.
Spread ice cream over layer.
Spread Cool Whip over ice cream.
Sprinkle pecans over whipped topping, and drizzle chocolate syrup over all.
Sprinkle reserved 3/4 cup cookie mixture over syrup.
Freeze for 2 to 3 hours.
Cover pan with foil.
Best if made 2 days in advance.

title: 5 star chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.

In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add eggs. Beat well. Combine flour, baking soda and salt. Gradually add to creamed mixture. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until very lightly browned.
Cool slightly, then remove.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: battered fish
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add cider vinegar; add water, a few drops at a time, to make a thick batter.
Pat fish dry and dip into batter.
Fry until golden.

title: blackened fish
directions: Thaw fish, if frozen. In a small mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients except margarine or butter. Brush both sides of fish with some of the melted margarine or butter; coat both sides with seasonings.

title: mexican casserole (2)
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain grease.
Season with salt, pepper, chili powder, and green chilies.
Add mushroom soup heat thoroughly.
Line casserole dish with broken tortillas.
Put half meat mixture over tortillas.
Sprinkle some grated cheese over meat.
Put another layer of tortillas and rest of meat and cheese. Bake at 350°F for 30 min.
Serve with hot sauce, lettuce salad, and a vegetable.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir together the last 3 ingredients and pour over salad.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Fresh frozen green peas (thawed) may also be added.

title: sweet and savory beans
directions: In 10-inch skillet, over medium heat, in hot margarine, cook onion until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add beans, syrup and mustard.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Makes 3 1/2 cups or 7 servings.

title: skillet spanish rice
directions: In skillet, brown rice, onion and garlic in butter.
Stir often.
Add meat, browning just until meat loses red color.
Stir occasionally.
Drain; stir in tomatoes and add other ingredients. Bring just to a boil.
Stir in green pepper.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Toss mixture well before serving.

title: ranch style beans and ground meat
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain off grease.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Add the beans and simmer about 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: plain cake
directions: Mix.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: big batch cookies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a bowl; beat with electric mixer until blended.
Add sugars; mix well.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to sugar mixture, beating until well blended.
Stir in cereal and remaining ingredients.
Drop by level tablespoonfuls on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until golden.
Cool slightly on cookie sheets; remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Yield:
9 dozen.

title: baked taco layered
directions: Spread chips in 9 x 13-inch pan (chopped).
Spread Mozzarella cheese over chips.
Spread cooked hamburg over cheese.
Sprinkle seasoning over hamburg.
Spread sour cream.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Top with lettuce, tomato, green pepper, onion, etc.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread cherry filling over bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Cover with pineapple and juice.
Sprinkle on dry cake mix.
Drizzle oleo over cake mix.
Sprinkle on coconut and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Melt butter and cheese in large heavy pan.
When melted, add sifted cocoa and sugar.
Beat with electric mixer.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Spread in large pan.
Cut in squares.

title: bubbling strawberry punch
directions: Thaw strawberries according to package directions.
Puree strawberries in a food processor or blender.
In large glass pitcher (about 2 quarts), combine strawberries, orange juice and Orange Ice Cubes.
Slowly add the sparkling water or seltzer. Garnish with orange slice.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix apples, celery and nuts. Toss with mayo and sour cream. Arrange on lettuce leaves; garnish with walnuts and cherries. Makes 4 servings.

title: *pastichio for the 90's 4
directions: Brown ground round and remove all fat. Season to taste.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine broccoli, celery and pimientos.
Mix well.
In a separate bowl, combine soup, sour cream, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well with broccoli mixture until well blended. Turn into 1 1/2-quart greased casserole pan. Sprinkle with cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until heated through and cheese bubbles.

title: the classic smoothie
directions: Pour the orange juice into a blender.
Add the bananas and strawberries.
Blend until smooth.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: italian cream cake(chocolate)
directions: Cream the margarine and shortening.
Add sugar and beat well. Add yolks and beat.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and baking powder and add to the creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla.
Add coconut and pecans.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Pour batter into three 9-inch greased cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes if using a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool and frost.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2 loaf pans that have been lined with wax paper and sprayed with Pam. (The sides of
the
pan should also be covered with Pam.) Cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate custard pie
directions: Melt cocoa and margarine together. Stir in flour and sugar; mix well. Beat eggs until fluffy. Then add to margarine mixture. Add vanilla and mix well. Pour into pie crust and bake at 300° for 40 minutes. Makes 2 pies.

title: lumpia
directions: Combine the first 12 ingredients, setting the egg white aside in a saucer.
Heat oil to 375°.
Place 2 tablespoons of filling in
1 corner of a single lumpia wrapper.
Roll up the wrapper, turning each end in like a Chinese spring roll or egg roll. Moisten
last
corner
with
egg white, so that it will stick. Place
roll
on
tray,
seam
side
down.
Cover
with plastic
as you
continue to roll the others.
Fry a few at a time
until golden brown.
Place on a cookie sheet, with paper towels,
in the oven on warm until all are fried.
Serve with banana sauce (optional), available at oriental food stores.

title: sharp cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve with crackers or potato chips.

title: margaret's chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken, celery, carrots and onion in salted water until chicken is tender.
Remove from water and dice chicken into bite-size pieces along with the carrots.
Mix the two cans of soup with 1 can of water.
Boil noodles as directed on package.

title: pea salad
directions: Open peas and drain.
Cut eggs and put peas, eggs, onions, Cheddar cheese and celery salt in bowl and mix in Miracle Whip. Chill and serve.

title: pfeffernuesse
directions: Cream the butter, anise flavoring and sugars.
Blend in egg. Add flour, salt and spices.
Blend thoroughly.
Stir in chopped almonds and citron.
Chill in refrigerator a few hours.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls using about a teaspoon of dough for each. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake in a 350° oven for about 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool a few minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream cheese; add marshmallow cream.
Blend well.
Add Cool Whip and blend well.
Serve with chunks of cantaloupe, honeydew melon, pineapple, apple, bananas, grapes, strawberries, etc.

title: simply great! pineapple blintzes
directions: Spoon the yogurt into a sieve lined with cheesecloth.
Place over a bowl and set aside to drain for 20 minutes.
Mix yogurt and pineapple in bowl; set aside.
Place egg whites in medium bowl and whisk until frothy.
Wisk in the milk and honey.
Add flour and baking powder; mix well.
Spray pan with Pam; allow pan to get warm.
Add about 1/4 cup batter to the pan and tilt the pan in all directions to spread the batter thinly all over bottom.
Cook 1 minute or until brown, browned the other side.
Place on wire rack to cool.
Repeat until all the batter is used.
To serve, divide the pineapple filling among this blintzes, spooning down the center of each.
Fold in the sides.
Makes 12.

title: saganaki(flaming greek cheese)
directions: Dip cheese slices into beaten egg to coat, then into flour seasoned with salt, pepper and m.s.g. to taste.
Coat skillet with olive oil and heat medium.
Place floured cheese in skillet; brown well on both sides.
Remove to heated platter.
Pour brandy that has been warmed over cheese and ignite.
Let flame a few seconds, then squeeze lemon juice over to extinguish.
Spread on small slices of Italian bread, sliced thin.

title: stuffed pepper for two
directions: Cut off top of peppers and clean out seeds.
Cook in boiling water to cover, 5 minutes.
Cook celery and onion in a little oil until tender.
Brown ground beef.
Add all ingredients together. Stuff the peppers with mixture.
Place in baking pan.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chicken tacquitos
directions: Cook chicken 2 minutes in oil.
Stir well.
Add onions and peppers; cook until chicken is done.
Drain; put aside.
Over medium heat, in same pan, put salsa and 6 ounces of Cheddar.
Cook and stir until cheese melts.
Add the chicken.
Break tacos into 4 pieces each.
Spoon 1 tablespoon mix onto shell; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 5
minutes, until cheese melts.
Makes 40 servings.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Crush cookies (all but 4 or so) and place across bottom of 9 x 13
pan.
Melt margarine and pour over cookie layer.
Combine pudding, milk, 1/2 of Cool Whip, and melted cream cheese.
Spread mixture over cookie layer.
Top layer is remaining Cool Whip and crumbs of saved cookies.
Cover and Refrigerate.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Combine first mix ingredients.
Heat 5 minutes.
Mix on medium speed of electric mixer or until smooth.
Fold in berries.
Pour filling in pastry shell.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Combine remaining ingredients, stirring well. Sprinkle over pie.
Bake 10 minutes more.
Chill before serving.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted margarine.
Pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Beat together for 15 minutes the eggs, margarine and confectioners sugar. Pour over crust.
Slice bananas thinly over this. Top with pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over this and top with pecans and/or cherries. Refrigerate.
Do not freeze.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all together with hand mixer.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: divinity fudge
directions: In a saucepan combine sugar, syrup and water.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Cook slowly without stirring to 265° or hard ball forms when dropped in cold water.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Wash potatoes and prick several times with fork.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Let cool.
Cut potatoes in half and scoop out pulp; set aside.
Discard skins.
