Melt butter in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickening and bubbly.
Add potato pulp, salt, pepper, 2 tablespoons green onions, 1/2 cup bacon and 1 cup cheese.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Stir in sour cream.
Add extra milk if necessary for desired thickness.
Serve with remaining onions, bacon and cheese.

title: aunt sally's tea cake cookies
directions: Blend sugar, eggs and butter until creamy.
Add flour to mixture.
Add baking powder and vanilla.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 350°.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Make up with cream or milk to the consistency of meat loaf. Bake at 400° until done.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Set oven for 350°.
Boil macaroni for about 10 minutes or until it is nearly done.
Drain.
In a 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish (sprayed with Pam), begin with a layer of cheese, then macaroni, then cheese, etc. until you end up with top layer cheese.
Pour egg mixture over the top of ingredients.
The egg mixture should be eggs, milk, Tabasco, salt and pepper.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes, then uncover and bake about 15 minutes more, until it begins to bubble and turn slightly brown.
I always sprinkle paprika over the top after pouring the liquid ingredients in before baking.
It adds more color to top.
Take out of oven and let it cool about 10 minutes.
Test to see if mixture has taken up the milk.
If it is too milky, you can take a basting tube and suck some of it out.
Usually the 10 to 15 minutes sitting out will do the trick.
ENJOY.
Serves 4.

title: party sandwiches
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger and drain.
Melt cheese in double boiler and add oregano, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well. Add meat to cheese mixture.
Spread on rye bread.
Makes 45. Great for parties.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: Mix cake mix, jello, eggs, milk, oil, strawberries, pecans and coconut. Pour into 3 greased and floured pans and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fold-over tortilla beef bake
directions: In skillet, cook beef and onions until meat is brown; drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes, enchilada sauce, cumin, salt, pepper and chili pepper.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour half of the meat sauce into a large, flat baking pan.
Spread tortilla with cream cheese and fold over and arrange on meat mixture.
Pour remaining meat mixture over this.
Top with grated Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until hot through.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Pinch up the angel food cake in a pan.
Mix jello up and pour over the cake.
Mash cake down so it soaks up in cake.
Put in freezer until jello gels.

title: acapulco eggs
directions: Cook tortillas in butter until golden brown; set aside.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid.
Add liquid to onion in skillet.
Cover and cook on high for 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in tomatoes, meat and green pepper; heat through.
Reduce heat to low.
Add tortillas and beaten eggs. Cover and cook 4 to 6 minutes, or until eggs are set.
Sprinkle with cheese; cover 1 minute until cheese melts.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: jalapeno cheese cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into buttered baking dish and bake at 425° for about 25 minutes or until done. This is a wonderful recipe.
It is particularly good with chicken, pork and any vegetable.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles in salted water until almost done (firm to the bite).
Drain and transfer to a buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Toss with half butter, salt and pepper.
Stir in cottage cheese and sour cream; dot with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Serves 4 to 6 as a main dish.
This recipe will not work with low-fat ingredients!

title: cheese ball
directions: Form ham into a ball and mold cream cheese around it and then roll in Cheddar cheese.

title: chocolate covered pretzels
directions: Fill glass or container with melting caps.
Heat in microwave for 30 seconds.
Stir until melted.
Continue every 30 seconds until completely melted.
Dip a pretzel rod into the chocolate and let excess drip off into cup.
Place on wax paper to dry.
Before they are completely dry, sprinkle with candy sprinkles.

title: pork tenderloin with mushroom
directions: Trim fat from pork.
Cut pork crosswise into 4 slices.
Place each slice between 2 sheets of waxed paper. Using the flat side of a meat mallet, pound lightly to 1/4-inch thickness.
Spray a cold medium skillet with nonstick coating. Preheat skillet.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and shred. Cook Rice-A-Roni per package directions. Add onion to rice while browning. Mix chicken, soups, pimento and cooked Rice-A-Roni. Mix well. Pour in 9 x 13 baking dish. Cook at 350° after topping with cheese and Ritz crackers. Cook until cheese bubbles.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Stir over low heat
the margarine, egg yolks and sugar in a skillet. Cook for 5 minutes.
Do not let it bubble or boil. Add dates and pecans.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies. Shape into balls and roll in coconut or powdered sugar.

title: paprika dumplings
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add shortening and milk; blend lightly.
Drop by spoonfuls on cooked macaroni or Chinese noodles.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tallerine
directions: Boil noodles in salted water until tender.
Brown in heavy skillet the ground beef, onion, garlic and pepper, then add chili powder, salt and pepper.
Line large greased casserole with half the noodles.
On top of the noodles, pour meat mixture.
Cover with corn and half cheese.
Add last half of noodles.
Over this pour diluted soup on top; pour Ro-Tel.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 250°, covered.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Can be frozen.

title: ingrid's banana bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Add sugar; mix well.
Sift together the flour and soda.
Add flour and egg alternately to the banana mixture. Add melted butter and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: maple eggnog punch
directions: In a large bowl, blend together eggnog, maple syrup and orange bitters.
Pour into chilled punch bowl.
Serve with dollops of whipped cream and nutmeg.

title: bisquick low calorie pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Spray a 9-inch deep pie pan.
Beat everything together for 2 minutes. Bake 50 minutes or until center puffs up.
(Check with knife.)
Makes its own crust.

title: low-fat apple turnovers
directions: Mix all filling ingredients; place stacked sheets of phyllo on flat surface and cover with plastic.
Wrap to keep from drying out.
Place 1 phyllo sheet on work surface.
Lightly coat with butter flavored nonstick coating spray.
Top with another sheet. Cut lengthwise in three 4-inch wide strips.
Move strips apart. Mound 1 heaping teaspoonful filling at one end about 1 inch from corner.
Fold opposite corner at same end over filling, forming a triangle.
Continue folding your way up the strip as you would a flag.
Repeat with the rest of filling and phyllo.
Heat oven to 400°; lightly coat cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 17 minutes.
Arrange turnovers seam side down.
Spray tops lightly with coating spray and top with cinnamon sugar.

title: kit kat bars
directions: In medium saucepan, mix crumbs, margarine, sugar and milk; bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Layer a third of the crackers in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour half the boiled mixture on top.
Put a second layer of crackers on top with remaining mixture.
Top with remaining third of crackers. Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips with peanut butter.
Spread over crackers.
Cool and cut.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen bars.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Combine with chopped onion.
Add grated carrot, sour cream, melted margarine and soup.
Top with stuffing mix.
Bake in uncovered casserole dish at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients, simmer half an hour.

title: fish chowder
directions: In small kettle, cut up haddock.
Cook until tender in 1/2 cup water; lay aside.
In large iron or heavy kettle, cut up onion, celery and potatoes.
Cook until tender in 2 cups water (salted). When tender, put in cooked fish.
Add salt, pepper, milk and butter.
Put on low flame until well heated.
Do not bring to a boil.

title: easy salmon
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly butter one 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
In a cup, combine salad dressing mix, water and lemon juice. Arrange salmon fillets in a single layer in the prepared baking dish.
Pour the water mixture over the top and place the sliced mushroom over the salmon.
Bake, covered, for 15 minutes.
Remove cover and bake for an additional 15 minutes, basting with cooking liquids.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Stir
together
oats, margarine and brown sugar.
Press mixture (reserve 1/4
cup for topping) into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Arrange bananas
over
crust.
Slice
ice
cream into 1/2-inch slices.
Place over bananas.
Sprinkle walnuts over ice cream. Freeze until firm.

title: cheese ball
directions: Work into a soft ball.
Roll in paprika and finely chopped pecans.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients until smooth.
Add peanuts and stir into melted chips.
Dollop by tablespoonfuls onto wax paper and chill until firm.

title: salad or dessert
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: all-at-once spaghetti dinner
directions: Cook and stir beef.
Add onion in a heavy 3-quart saucepan until meat loses red color.
Stir in seasoning.
Pour in 3 cans of tomato sauce and water.
Bring to boil.
Break uncooked spaghetti in half.
Sprinkle in a little at a time, stirring into the sauce. Cover tightly and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes over low heat. Stir in Cheddar cheese until cheese is melted.

title: squash casserole
directions: Parboil squash until tender.
Saute onion, celery and pepper in oleo.
Add squash to this.
Add eggs and cream of celery soup. Mix with cracker crumbs.
Place in casserole and bake at 350° for 25 minutes, then add grated cheese on top and return to oven for 8 minutes longer.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil on low heat. Add peanut butter; stir until peanut butter melts. Pour over Rice Krispies in large bowl; mix well. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and pat down firmly.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Chill dough.
Roll out and cut into shapes with cookie cutter.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: strawberry angel cake
directions: Crumble angel food cake in bottom of 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Then top with instant pudding as directed on box.
Add strawberries and glaze and place on top of pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: spinach with pine nuts and raisins
directions: Bring a large pot of water to a boil.
Blanch spinach by dropping in water for 45 seconds.
Drain spinach; chop and set aside.

title: caramel pecan squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place cake mix in large bowl.
Using pastry blender or fork, cut in 1/4 cup butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press in bottom of ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Top with pecans.
In large saucepan, combine brown sugar, sugar, 1 cup butter and honey.
Bring to a full boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 3 minutes; remove from heat.
Stir in whipping cream until well blended.
Pour evenly over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 17 to 22 minutes or until entire surface is bubbly.
Cool completely.
Cut into squares or bars.
Makes 48 bars.

title: beef bake
directions: Mix and put in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Stir occasionally.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: banana smoothie
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender or food processor. Blend until smooth. Makes 1 serving.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Whip the cream cheese until smooth then add the milk a little at a time until all the milk has been added. Add pudding and beat until mixture thickens.

title: parsleyed new potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Cook in boiling salted water 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain.
Peel if desired.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in parsley and lemon juice.
Pour over hot potatoes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: ranch potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes, then drain and mix all the other ingredients in a serving bowl until all is coated.
Chill and serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Crush bananas
and add sugar, shortening and eggs.
Mix well. Add flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add nuts last (stirred
in
a
little
flour to keep separated in batter).

title: plum muffins
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into well-greased mini muffin tins, filling 1/2 full.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: pear relish
directions: Combine all.
Cook for 35 to 40 minutes.
Seal in hot jars.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Flour chicken thighs.
Brown in small amount of oleo and oil. Arrange in casserole.
In same pan saute onions and celery. Sprinkle over chicken the onions and celery and peas and corn.
Mix soups and milk.
Pour this mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle with sweet paprika.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix all together.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: cabbage burgers
directions: Cook ground turkey; drain.
Shred cabbage and onions; microwave these 2 ingredients for 15 minutes.
Mix together.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Roll the roll mix into circle; break into "big" golf ball size pieces.
Add 1 large spoon of meat mixture.
Gather edges; put inverted onto sprayed cookie sheet. Let rise.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: sesame seed cookies
directions: Lightly toast sesame seed and coconut light brown.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add egg, flavoring and toasted seed and coconut. Shape in balls (1 teaspoon).
Place on greased cookie sheet. Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mock sour cream
directions: Combine in blender.
Cover and run on high speed until completely smooth, about 10 seconds.
One tablespoon contains 15 calories.
Yield: 1 1/2 cups.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Put drained cabbage in buttered dish.
Pour remaining ingredients over cabbage.
Cook until brown at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mom's pineapple banana nut cake
directions: Assemble all ingredients before mixing.
Chill bananas after dicing.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Roll crust and fit to pie pan.
Break crackers coarsely into the pie shell. Combine water, sugar and cream of tartar in saucepan and boil gently for 15 minutes.
Add lemon juice.
Cool. Pour syrup over crackers.
Dot generously with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Put top crust on.
Seal edges.
Cut slits.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Then add Roquefort cheese. Place in container with tight fitting lid.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Makes an excellent salad dressing or vegetable dip.

title: basic pie filling
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until it starts to get thick, then add either coconut, chocolate or lemon and continue cooking until real thick.
Use 2 egg whites for meringue.

title: creamy red beans
directions: Cook red beans 1 1/2 to 2 hours under low fire with ham hocks. Add seasonings after 2 hours of cooking, then let simmer for about 2 hours or until creamy. Serve with rice. Makes about 20 servings.

title: nibblin' fish
directions: Mix together the Cheerios, pretzels, crackers and peanuts. Combine oil and Worcestershire sauce; pour over cereal mix.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: baked french toast(wholesome breakfast; makes 10 slices)
directions: In a shallow dish, combine eggs, milk, vanilla, sugar and cinnamon.
Dip bread slices into milk mixture, coating both sides. Allow excess to drain.
Place slices on a nonstick baking sheet. Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 10 minutes on each side or until golden brown.

title: fresh baked ham
directions: Wash ham thoroughly; place in large kettle.
Cover with water and cook slowly until tender (20 to 30 minutes per pound).
Remove from kettle and remove the skin.
Score and sprinkle with brown sugar and dot with cloves.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°, basting with cider.

title: refrigerator dill pickles
directions: Boil together water, vinegar, salt and sugar to make a brine. Pour over cucumbers in jar.
Refrigerate 1 week.

title: dirty rice
directions: In 1 qt or bigger saucepan, melt butter. Add vegetables, worcestershire sauce, and garlic powder. Saute until tender. Add rice and water; bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed. Serves 6.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Mix all together and spread in a 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans.
Then press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, then cool.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine eggs and pumpkin.
Blend in sugar, spice, flour and salt.
Mix well.
Add milk and mix well.
Pour into pastry shell. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes one pie (8 servings).
May double for 2 pies.

title: cranberry pork chops
directions: Trim fat from chops.
Rub chop with pepper.
Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium-high heat. Add chops and cook until browned on both sides.
Add 3 tablespoons water to skillet.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 25 to 30 minutes until tender.

title: lo-cal carrot nibbles
directions: Cut carrots into 3-inch long and 1/4-inch wide strips.
Saute garlic and chopped onion in oil over low heat until soft.
Stir in vinegar, salt, mustard and pepper.
Add spice bag; bring to a boil.
Add carrot strips; cover and simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Carrots should remain crisp and crunchy.
Discard spice bag.
Transfer carrot mixture to shallow dish.
Top with layer of onion rings.
Cover and refrigerate until needed, basting occasionally.
The longer they marinate, the better.
Onions are tasty, too.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: sausage cornbread dressing
directions: Combine sausage, onions and celery in a large skillet. Cook over medium heat, stirring until sausage is crumbled. Drain well. Combine cornbread and next 4 ingredients in a large bowl. Stir in sausage mixture. Add broth and eggs, stirring well. Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until browned. Yield: 10 to 12 servings (9 cups).

title: dump cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13 inch pan with Pam.
Layer the ingredients in the order listed into the pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes - 1 hour.

title: walnut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie pan and bake at 350° until done.

title: broccoli and corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fancy franks
directions: Mix mustard and jelly in saucepan. Place on low heat. Add wieners to sauce and cook until heated through.

title: cheese pockets
directions: Mix together thoroughly cream cheese, butter and flour.
Form into ball and refrigerate overnight.
Leave at room temperature about 1 hour.
Roll out thin on lightly floured board.
Cut into about 3-inch rounds.
Fill with 1 teaspoon jam or jelly (your desired flavor).
Fold over and seal edges by crimping with fork. Bake on cookie sheet at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool and dust with powdered sugar.

title: easy sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until somewhat firm. Meanwhile, bring milk and butter to just a boil, then remove.
Add salt, flour, baking powder and vanilla to egg mixture, then beat in milk mixture. Pour into greased square pan.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean, approximately 20 to 30 minutes.

title: squash relish
directions: Soak squash in saltwater for at least 3 hours, then drain. Bring vinegar, sugar, turmeric, celery seed and mustard seed to a boil. Add squash, chopped bell peppers, chopped onions and pimento; bring to boil again. Let boil for a minute or more. Pack into canning jars and seal.

title: cherry dream pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and Dream Whip until smooth.
Pour in pie crusts.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Quarter potatoes.
Combine the dry ingredients in a plastic bag.
Shake potatoes in mixture.
Put on a baking sheet and drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, turning halfway through.

title: n.y. style cheesecake
directions: Cream the sugar and cream cheese until smooth; don't overbeat. Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend until smooth. Don't overbeat.
Fold in sour cream. Set aside.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions, 3 egg recipe, plus add pudding.
Bake according to box.
Poke holes in warm cake; pour coconut milk over cake.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Serves 12. Very easy and good.

title: white batter bread
directions: Place milk in saucepan and scald. Remove from heat. Add sugar, margarine and salt. Set this milk mixture aside to cool to lukewarm. Next, pour water into a large bowl; sprinkle yeast over water and stir to dissolve thoroughly. Add milk mixture to water mixture and stir. Next, gradually add flour. Batter will be stiff. Beat for approximately 2 minutes until well mixed. Cover. Let rise in warm place free of draft for approximately 50 minutes or until double in bulk. Beat down and beat for 1/2 minute. Turn onto greased bread pan. Bake in 375° oven for 45 to 50 minutes until nicely browned and hollow to the touch.

title: corn pudding
directions: Toss corn and cheese in bowl.
Separate eggs and set whites aside.
Whisk together yolks, butter, cream, sugar, salt, pepper and cayenne.
Stir in jalapenos.
Pour over corn and cheese, blending well.
Whisk egg whites to form soft peaks.
Fold into corn mixture.
Transfer to buttered baking dish and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until surface is brown and center is set.
Let sit 10 minutes before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute butter, onion, bell pepper and water chestnuts.
Fold in Cheddar cheese, mayonnaise, sugar and egg.
Add salt and pepper. Grease a casserole dish.
Pour ingredients into casserole dish. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cauliflower bacon salad
directions: In large salad bowl, layer lettuce pieces, then crumbled bacon, chopped onion and end with cauliflower.
In small bowl, blend real mayonnaise and sugar.
Pour dressing over salad; do not stir.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Stir and serve immediately. This salad will not keep once stirred.

title: burnt-sugar cake
directions: Gradually add sugar to shortening, creaming thoroughly. Add vanilla, then eggs, one at a time, beating one minute after each. Add sifted dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with water, a small amount at a time, beating smooth after each addition. Add 3 Tbsp. Burnt-sugar syrup.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower into small flowerets.
Mix all together.
Will keep 3 to 4 days in refrigerator.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Mix soy sauce, egg and meal.
Roll pork in mixture.
Fry until brown, 15 minutes or so and set aside.
Drain pineapple, saving liquid.
Combine brown sugar and cornstarch.
Add pineapple juice, vinegar, soy sauce and salt.
Stir and cook over low heat until thick and clear.
Add pork, pineapple and pepper.
Simmer about 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, powdered sugar and peanut butter with a fork.
Add the Cool Whip gradually, about 2 or 3 heaping tablespoons at a time.
Put into baked pie shell and put in freezer for several hours.
Once cut, refrigerate.

title: nacho cheese chips
directions: Optional:
Top with mushrooms or sliced jalapeno peppers.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, coconut and salt. Add milk and vanilla; mix well (batter will be stiff). Drop by tablespoonful 1-inch apart onto a greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Remove to wire rack to cool. Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: ground beef oriental
directions: Brown onions and celery in butter.
Remove from pan.
Brown rice and ground beef; set aside.
Combine soups, water, soy sauce and pepper.
Add ground beef, onions, celery and rice.
Stir in bean sprouts.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.
Serve with warmed Chinese noodles. Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Use 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Mix sugar, eggs and butter until very smooth.
Add bananas, cut in slices and mix again.
Blend in rest of ingredients.
If desired, add raisins or chocolate chips at the end.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 1 hour. Let cool completely before slicing.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix flour, soda and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in layers at 350° until a toothpick comes out clean.
Ice cake when cool.

title: stuffed shrimp
directions: Saute green onions and garlic until partly done in olive oil. Add shelled, clean shrimp. Stir and cook 3 minutes or so.
Add dash of white wine and sprinkle with paprika.
Serve over linguini or noodles or rice.

title: biblical cake
directions: Check your Bible for regular ingredients.
Season to taste with Chronicles 9:9.
Mix like any other fruit cake, will keep indefinitely.

title: fresh cream-style corn
directions: Remove shucks and silks from corn and wash.

Using a very sharp thin-bladed knife, cut off very tops of kernels and scrape out cream from inside kernels. Combine all of corn and water. Cook in a very heavy skillet on low heat, stirring often, until corn is thick and a golden yellow color.
Add oleo and salt to taste.

title: lettuce dressing
directions: Boil slowly.
Use over lettuce, hot or cold.
Refrigerates well for several days.

title: fucilli
directions: Fry Italian sausage; remove from skillet and drain on paper towels.
Add onion, bell pepper and garlic to skillet and cook until done.
Add mushrooms to skillet and cook 2 minutes, tossing lightly.
Put everything, including cooked pasta and spaghetti sauce, in 4-quart pot.
Mix and reheat.
May add Parmesan cheese.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare macaroni according to directions.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper; beat well.
In casserole dish put a layer of cooked macaroni and a layer of grated cheese.
Cover with egg and milk mixture.
Add another layer of macaroni and cheese mixture until all has been used.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Melt 1/4 cup of butter in a skillet.
Brown meatballs. Remove meatballs from skillet and drain well.
Melt remaining 1/4 cup of butter, add flour and stir.
Cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in beef broth and water.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add sour cream; reduce heat, stir well.
Add meatballs, heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: english toffee
directions: Bring to a boil all ingredients, except nuts and chocolate chips, until mixture starts to change color. Lower temperature. Stir constantly until brittle 310° on candy thermometer.
Add 1 cup nuts. Pour into greased cookie sheet.
When firm, add chocolate chips on top and spread.
When cold, break into pieces.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix cheese, juice and sugar together.
Add whipped topping. Pour into cooled baked pie shell. Chill.
Add cherry pie filling on top.

title: lima casserole
directions: Cook beans according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in skillet; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add milk; cook over medium heat until thickened.
Add salt, pepper, catsup, pimento and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts; set aside.

title: hillbilli chili
directions: Brown the hamburger and sausage in a skillet; drain grease. Brown onion, mushrooms and green pepper in butter.
Put all the ingredients into a large crock-pot and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours, on high for 3 to 4 hours.
Low is best!
Stir every hour. Serve and enjoy!

title: apricot jello mold(servings:  8)
directions: Add Jell-O to boiling water and dissolve.
Pour into blender and add apricots and cream cheese.
Blend well.
Pour into mold that has been sprayed.
Refrigerate until set.

title: no-fat cucumber salad
directions: Slice cucumbers.
Squeeze lemon juice over all.
Sprinkle with seasonings to taste.
Serve on a bed of red tip leafy lettuce.

title: french icing
directions: Cook flour and milk over medium heat, stirring constantly until it starts to thicken.
Reduce heat to low and continue to stir until thick and smooth.
Remove from heat and let cool.
This has to be cooked slow so it won't get lumpy.
Cream together shortening and margarine.
Then add to flour mixture and mix well.
Add vanilla.
Add sugar.

title: creamsicle cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until fluffy. Beat in eggs, sour cream and vanilla. Put 1 cup mixture into a small bowl and add extract and colorings. Spoon plain mixture into pie shell. Swirl colored mixture through it.

title: honey orange carrots
directions: Combine carrots, orange juice, honey, margarine and nutmeg. Cook over medium heat until mixture boils.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Uncover and cook 5 to 10 minutes, until carrots are cooked and mixture has thickened.
Stir in parsley and serve.

title: mama's cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together using enough buttermilk to make a medium batter.
Pour in hot skillet with bacon drippings, sprinkled with meal to keep from sticking.
Bake in a 400° oven about 30 minutes.

title: nut and honey stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken into thin strips; set aside.
Mix orange juice, honey, soy sauce, cornstarch and grated fresh ginger in a small bowl.
Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in a wok or large skillet.
Add chicken pieces; stir-fry until white and opaque, about 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from wok.
Add additional tablespoon of oil to wok; stir-fry celery, sweet potato and broccoli over high
heat until crisp-tender.
Return chicken strips to pan along with orange juice mixture.
Cook and stir
over medium-high heat until thickened.
Sprinkle with nuts and sliced green onions.
Spoon over rice.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Boil
potatoes	with
jackets
on.
Put in refrigerator until cool.
Peel.
Grate and add other ingredients.
Put into baking dish
and
bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: fried okra
directions: Wash okra; trim ends and slice while still damp. Roll okra in cornmeal with salt. Heat oil in frying pan. Add okra; cook on medium heat until brown, stirring often.

title: spinach dip in bread bowl
directions: Mix salad dressing, sour cream and salad dressing mix until well blended. Add spinach, water chestnuts and red pepper.
Mix well. Refrigerate.

title: chocolate scotchoroos
directions: Measure corn syrup and sugar into large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until sugar dissolves and mixture begins to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter, mix well.
Add rice Krispies.
Stir until well coated.
Press mixture into 13 X 9 X 2inch pan coated with cooking spray.
Set aside.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Pop corn in a brown paper bag.
Cook sugar, butter, syrup and salt in a deep dish 5 minutes in microwave oven, making sure brown sugar is dissolved.
Pour syrup over popped corn in a paper bag; roll top of bag shut.
Place in microwave oven 1 1/2 minutes. Remove and shake.
Return to oven for 1 minute.
Remove and shake. Return to oven for another 1/2 minute.
Pour onto a cookie sheet to cool.

title: creamy chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Spray a 2 1/2-quart casserole with nonstick cooking spray. Combine in the casserole the rice, soup, skim milk and lemon juice.
Stir to combine.
Fold in chicken, broccoli and water chestnuts.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until rice is cooked and cheese is melted.
Makes 6 (1 1/2-cup) servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Stir first 3 ingredients and set aside. Mix together sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add one egg at a time, then milk. Add remaining dry ingredients gradually. Add banana.
Makes 4 mini loaves or 1 large loaf.
Bake mini loaves 25 minutes or large loaf 55 to 60 minutes.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Cream together sugar, oil and eggs.
Add flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Fold in coconut, nuts, apples and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: goodie bars
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup milk.
Set aside; keep warm.
Add margarine and milk to cake mix and mix well.
Pour half in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and pecans and drizzle caramel mixture over this.
Put rest of cake mix over that and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: taco pie
directions: In large frypan, brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix and water.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Place triangles in ungreased 9 or 10-inch pie pan, pressing to form a crust.
Sprinkle 1 cup corn chips over bottom of crust.
Spoon meat mixture over crust and corn chips.
Spread sour cream over meat mixture; cover with cheese.
Sprinkle on remaining corn chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until crust is golden brown.
Serve wedges topped with shredded lettuce.
May also top with salsa.

title: impossible pie
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; let cool.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar and butter, mixing well.
Add flour, coconut and milk; mix well.
Pour mixture into two 9-inch pie plates.
Cook for 35 minutes at 350°. This makes its own crust.

title: virginia pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and Crisco.
Add eggs one at a time, beating with mixer after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Alternate with milk; beat until fluffy. Add vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured large Bundt pan or tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all together.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind cranberries in food processor to fine.
Add oranges; grind until mixed well.
Put into glass bowl; add sugar, mix well. Add nuts if you want.
Store in refrigerator overnight.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix flour and sugar. Stir in egg and liquid. Cook over medium heat until it thickens. Cool. When cool, fold into 1/2 pint cream whipped and 1 cup Cool Whip. Spread on hardened jello.

title: tomato pie main dish
directions: Prick bottom
and
sides
of pastry shell; bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Set aside to cool.

title: apple spice custard cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as package directs; stir in apples.
Pour into well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean.

title: ice cream cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk and flavoring.
Beat well.
Add flour.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
If desired, decorate with candied fruits or nuts, etc.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen cookies.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Melt Milky Way bars in milk.
Beat eggs and add to milk mixture.
Blend all other ingredients with milk mixture.
Pour into freezer container and finish filling with milk.
Freeze.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: glazed microwave chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken breast halves with paprika.
Place 2 lemon slices on each part and arrange chicken in a circular microwave dish with meaty area toward outside and ribs toward center.
Cover loosely with wax paper and microwave on High about 10 minutes, turning dish after 5 minutes.

title: chocolate cake for chocolate lovers
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Combine chocolate with 1 cup of butter and melt slowly in a double boiler. Remove from heat and add eggs one at a time, beaten well with a wooden spoon after each addition. Continue mixing while adding sugar, then flour.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Measure flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt into a bowl.
Blend in milk and shortening.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Stir together the brown sugar and 1 1/4 cups cocoa; sprinkle over batter.
Pour hot water over batter. Bake for 45 minutes.
While hot, cut into squares. Invert onto plate or bowl and spoon sauce over each serving.
Top with whipped cream.
Makes 9 servings.
Bake in a 350° oven.

title: beef-noodle casserole
directions: Brown beef; add onion, celery and green pepper.
Brown all ingredients and add cooked noodles.
Add all of soups, except 1/2 can of tomato; pour remainder of soup over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: karen's banana pudding
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and cook over medium heat until thick.
Layer wafers and bananas.
Pour mixture over bananas and wafers and let cool.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Chill bowl.
Mix Big Red and Sprite.
Add strawberries, partially thawed.
Serve.
Scoops of ice cream may be added to punch before serving.

title: mrs. t's fried chicken coating
directions: Combine all ingredients well. Coat chicken pieces well.
Brown in oil.
Put chicken in a large shallow baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until chicken is tender. This makes enough coating for 3 chickens.
Unused portions of dry mix can be stored in a sealed glass jar.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate with butter over low heat, stirring until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Gradually add milk.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt thoroughly.
Beat eggs and flavoring into dry ingredients.
Gradually blend in chocolate mixture.
Pour into pie shells.

title: cinnamon filled cookies
directions: In a small bowl, stir together oleo and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy on low speed.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Divide into 24 balls.
In ungreased baking sheet, put 12 balls.
Use small juice glass to make wide round depressions in center, leaving a rim.
Fill with topping.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan to waxed paper.
Cool and drizzle icing over cookies.

title: barnyard cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together until fluffy: almond extract, shortening, brown sugar, milk, vanilla and egg.

title: vegetable marinated carrots
directions: Slice carrots thin and boil in salted water for 10 minutes or until barely tender.
Drain and layer with other vegetables, finishing with carrots on top.
Put tomato soup, oil, vinegar and sugar in saucepan and bring to boil.
Pour over carrots and refrigerate.
Will keep 2 weeks to 1 month if kept covered and refrigerated.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Pare and slice potatoes thin.
Make white sauce of butter or margarine, flour and milk.
Put half the potatoes in a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with half the sauce, seasonings and onion.
Then put the rest of potatoes in and add rest of the sauce. Cover and bake in a 350° oven about 1 hour.
Uncover and continue baking until top is brown.
Grated cheese may be added to white sauce if desired.

title: fudgy chip bars
directions: In medium bowl, combine cookies, flour, coconut and chocolate chips.
Stir in spread, condensed milk and vanilla extract. Spread into greased 8 or 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or lightly browned around edges.
Cool; sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cut into bars.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: monkey bread
directions: In Shaker bag, put in sugar and cinnamon. Mix well. Place quartered biscuits in bag, shake until all coated. Dump into a greased tube pan. (if not Teflon). In saucepan, put butter, sugar and cinnamon. Boil 2-3 min. Pour over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 30 min. Let cool for 10 min.
then serve.

title: *rum buns
directions: Prepare roll mix as directed on package.
After first rising, roll dough into a 10 x 12-inch rectangle.
Combine rum extract, powdered sugar and water; mix until smooth.
Spread soft butter and half of the powdered sugar mixture over the dough.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll as jelly roll, starting with long side.
Cut in 18 (1-inch) slices.

title: linda salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello in 2 cups of hot water.
Add the large marshmallows and cream cheese (softened is easier).
Stir until melted (over low heat, if necessary), then place in refrigerator until it begins to gel.
Add pineapple (drained).
Add chopped pecans and maraschino cherries.
Fold in whipped whipping cream. Return to refrigerator until congealed.

title: greek pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta.
Add chopped vegetables, and then all remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and chill.
If desired, add more vinegar to taste.

title: sweet pickled beets
directions: Select small young beets or 1/4 larger.
Wash and leave 3 inches of tops on and roots.
Cook until skins slip off easily (about 15 minutes).
Add all ingredients together and boil into a syrup.
Pack beets into jars to within 1/2 inch of top (using pint jars).
Pour boiling syrup over beets to top of them.
Process 30 minutes in boiling water bath.
Also known as cold packing.

title: italian-style chicken roll-up
directions: Pour about half of the spaghetti sauce in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside.
Brown chicken in butter over medium heat about 15 minutes, turning once.
Drain on paper towel. Cut cheese slices in halves.
Wrap each piece of chicken with 1 slice of cheese and 1 slice of ham, securing with wooden toothpicks.
Place in baking dish.
Pour remaining spaghetti sauce over top.
Sprinkle with mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: brown sugar pecan rounds
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, brown sugar and egg.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by teaspoonful, about 2 inches apart, on greased baking sheet.
(Dough will flatten and spread.) Yields 3 dozen.

title: caraway cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer.
Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm.
Serve with wheat or rye crackers.
Yields 2 cups. Contains 65 calories per tablespoon.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Blend together oleo, flour and nuts.
Spread in bottom and part way up sides of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: beef salami
directions: Mix together in a bowl, all ingredients.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate 24 hours.
Mix again; divide into 4 portions and roll each in Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate
24 hours more.
Unwrap and place on a rack so it will drip.
(Put aluminum wrap in bottom of oven.)
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until turns red.

title: gram's fresh strawberry pie
directions: Boil 1 cup strawberries, water, sugar and cornstarch until thickened.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Fill crust with remaining 1 1/2 quarts of strawberries.
Top with whipped cream.

title: enchilada sauce
directions: Melt shortening; brown garlic.
Add flour and chili powder. Cook for a few minutes, then add tomato juice and 2 quarts water. Add seasoning.
Bring to slow boil.
Add other quart of water to desired thickness.
It is better if cooked slowly.
Freezes well!

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and potato chips together. Place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Cover top of casserole with cheese, then spread potato chips over cheese.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: italian baked chicken
directions: Combine salad dressing mix, butter and mustard.
Baste chicken before placing in oven then every 15 minutes for 1 hour. Bake at 400°.

title: johnnycake
directions: Makes 4 cuts for two.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients but butter and cream in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Cook for a few minutes until it thickens a little. Remove from heat.
Add the butter.
You can add either sweet or sour cream to make one pint, if desired.

title: sticky buns
directions: Thaw bread dough; roll out, spread with margarine and sprinkle with cinnamon and brown sugar.
Roll up and cut into 9 pieces. Put into greased 9-inch square pan.
(Nuts may be put in bottom of pan.)
Mix and melt margarine, brown sugar, vanilla pudding, milk and cinnamon.
Pour over raised dough and let raise 2 hours more. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (325° for glass baking dish).
Remove from pan.

title: chicken baked pork chops
directions: Season chops and brown in frypan.
Put	chops
in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish and spoon uncooked rice on each chop.
Mix soup with
milk
and
drippings
in frying pan.
Pour over the chops and rice.
Cover and bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: jambalaya
directions: Brown hamburger or ham lightly and cook out some of the grease.
Remove meat from fat and pour off excess grease.
In remaining grease saute chopped onions, celery and bell pepper until onion is clear.
Add raw rice, tomatoes, bay leaf, thyme, oregano, salt, pepper, garlic and water to cover.
Cover and cook slowly until rice is done, being careful not to let it stick. Sprinkle top with chopped parsley before serving.

title: crazy cake
directions: Place ingredients in bowl and beat at low speed just so it is mixed.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serves a large group of people.

title: cucumber and cream cheese sandwiches
directions: Mash the cheese with a fork or heavy wooden spoon, thinning the consistency with a bit of mayonnaise or milk.
Work in the grated pulp after wringing it dry in a paper napkin or paper towel.
Blend in the onion cautiously, tasting to make sure that the flavor enhances and does not overpower the delicate cucumber taste.
Add salt and pepper or hot sauce to taste.
Keep stirring until a good texture for spreading or dipping.
A few drops of green coloring may be added.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix squash and salt.
Let drain 15 minutes, then squeeze out excess liquid.
Mix all other ingredients and squash together. Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil and fry until brown.
Drain on paper towels. These are good.

title: granny's poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Place in baking dish.
Melt butter in pan and crumble Ritz crackers and stir until butter is absorbed.
Put buttered crumbs on top of chicken and sprinkle poppy seed on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: betty's apricot jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add cold water.
Stir in marshmallows and cream cheese; mix well.
Add pineapple, nuts and Cool Whip.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan and chill.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak the beans overnight.
Cook until the skins pull back. Let the beans stand one hour in the liquid.
Drain and place beans in a crock-pot.
Combine all other ingredients and mix.
Cover and cook on low heat for 10 to 12 hours or cook on high for 4 to 6 hours.
The best method is to cook on high for 3 hours and then lower temperature.
Stir occasionally.

title: beef or deer jerky
directions: Mix all together; let meat marinate for 12 hours in mixture. Take out of mixture and bake on wire screen or hang by toothpicks for 5 to 8 hours until dry.

title: easy cinnamon buns
directions: Thaw bread dough.
In a saucepan, put water, oleo, brown sugar and cinnamon; boil for 2 minutes.
Pour mixture in large cake pan. Pull off hunks of bread dough.
Drop them into mixture; put aside to raise.
Bake at 350° until top is browned.
Turn upside down on cookie sheet.

title: old-time tomato preserves
directions: Peel and quarter tomatoes.
Cover with sugar.
Allow to stand overnight.
Drain off syrup.
Heat to a boil.
Cook until syrup spins a thread (232°).
Add tomatoes and orange and lemon slices. Cook over low heat until tomato is transparent.
Seal in hot, sterilized glasses.
Makes 12 (6 ounce) glasses.

title: leek and potato soup
directions: Wash leeks carefully to clean off all dirt or sand.
Dice potatoes; slice leeks thinly.
Simmer the leeks and potatoes together with chicken stock, salt and pepper for 40 to 50 minutes. Mash the vegetables, or puree them in a blender or food processor.
Check seasonings and reheat, adding the cream.
Garnish with parsley.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: luscious cheese cake
directions: Beat cheeses together; add sugar at low speed.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Stir in flour and cornstarch.
Add butter and sour cream, then the beaten eggs.
Pour into a slightly greased spring-form pan 10 x 2 1/2-inches.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Turn oven off and leave for approximately 2 additional hours.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Add all ingredients to melted butter. Mix well.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Combine cake mix, margarine and beaten eggs.
This will make a very thick batter.
Pat into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan (greased and floured).
Then combine the remaining ingredients. Pour this on top of the batter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook ground beef with onion until meat loses color and onion is clear.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sweetened condensed milk, pudding mix & choco bake.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into ready made crust.
Drizzle with warmed hot fudge, sprinkle with almonds. Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: ripe tomato catsup
directions: Combine tomatoes, onions, peppers and salt; let stand 3 hours. Put mixture in cloth sack or jelly bag.
Let drain overnight. Combine tomato mixture with sugar, vinegar and allspice; boil for 2 minutes.
Pack into hot pint jars.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all together with flour, enough to make it drop off spoon thick. Fry in oil in skillet or in Fry Daddy.

title: angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour and confectioners sugar.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar in a large bowl on medium speed.
Beat in sugar on high speed, 2 tablespoons at a time.
Beat until stiff and glossy.
Add salt and vanilla. Sprinkle flour and sugar mixture, 1/4 cup at a time.
Cut through batter with metal spatula after pouring into tube pan.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Cool upside down for 1 1/2 hours.

title: party munchies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut up 1/2 stick oleo and place on cookie sheet to melt in oven.
When melted, spread out pecan halves.
Bake for approximately 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. In a skillet, melt 1 stick of oleo.
Take off heat and add boxes of DooDads or Chex mix, Parmesan cheese, oregano, garlic salt and garlic powder.
Stir thoroughly.
Let cool before sealing in bag or container.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: * May use shredded chicken (cooked) or ground beef.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in microwave as usual.
Combine soups with 1 can milk and 1 can water; cook in a large saucepan.
Add margarine, salt and pepper.
Add cooked broccoli to warm soup.
Add cheese slices (one slice at a time), stirring the mixture as each slice melts.
Soup will thicken.

title: picnic casserole
directions: Brown the hamburg; add onions and peppers.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and simmer 10 minutes.
Add potato water, sliced potatoes, salt and pepper and butter.
Pour into greased casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: birds nest cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add egg yolks, flour and vanilla; mix well.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Dip each ball into egg whites, then into finely chopped nuts.
Put indentation in ball with your thumb.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet in 350° oven for 5 minutes.
Remove and put bit of jam in center of each cookie and continue baking until brown, about 10 more minutes. Makes 84 cookies.

title: lemon and cheese jello salad
directions: Stir water, Jell-O and marshmallows together until melted; cool.
In saucepan, combine eggs, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Cook over medium heat until thick; cool and mix with first mixture. Add crushed pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip; add grated American cheese over top.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: easy au gratin potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Spray 8-inch baking dish or 1 1/2-quart casserole with nonstick spray. In a large bowl, combine sour cream and soup; mix well. Add potatoes, cheese and onions; mix well. Spoon mixture into dish; cover with foil and bake 45 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix well and set overnight.

title: scripture cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add sugar, lard, 2 cups raisins and 3/4 cup milk.
Mix until all flour is dampened.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add 3 unbeaten eggs and 1/4 cup milk.
Beat 1 minute. Bake at 375° in a tube pan.

title: family chicken dinner
directions: Mix soup, dressing and preserves and pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8 people.
Make yellow rice as a side dish.

title: freezer cucumber pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onion and celery together in large bowl.
Mix sugar, salt, pepper and vinegar together but do not heat.
Pour this mixture over cucumbers.
Put in refrigerator.
Stir everyday for 4 days.
Put in containers and freeze.

title: cheese & chicken enchiladas
directions: Melt margarine in frying pan. Cook onion until tender. Add chicken, cream cheese, cumin and 1 cup picante sauce. Stir until hot and the cream cheese melts. Stir in 2 cups shredded sharp cheese until melted. Place one tortilla shell on plate. Spoon about 1/3 cup chicken mixture in a line on the shell. Roll up and place seam side down in an oblong baking pan. Repeat with remaining tortillas. After all shells are fixed, pour remaining picante sauce over top and cover with remaining shredded cheese. Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: swiss bliss
directions: Melt oleo
in
bottom
of large pan (10 x 13-inch). Put meat atop
butter,
then
onion soup mix on each serving, followed by mushrooms,	green
pepper
and tomatoes.
To the reserved tomato juice, add enough V-8 juice to make 5 cups.
Mix in the sauce and cornstarch.
Pour over meat mixture and cover with foil.
Bake
for	3 to 4 hours or until meat is fork-tender.

title: dumplings(chicken)
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add milk and oil to make a soft dough. Drop soft dough by tablespoon in hot gravy.
Cover with lid and cook over low heat for 20 minutes.
Do not remove lid until cooking time is up.
Self-rising flour may be used, omitting salt and baking powder.
These are light and fluffy.

title: iced tea
directions: Start with cold water in a small saucepan and add tea.
Let it get hot, but do not boil.
Cover and steep at least 15 minutes. Fill 1/2 gallon pitcher half full with cold water.
Stir in 1 cup of sugar (more, if desired).
Pour hot tea in pitcher of water; finish filling pitcher with water.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Cook on stove for 20 minutes, then refrigerate overnight.
Add leftover roast (cut up) to sauce and cook until heated.
Serve on buns.

title: ham slices with corn bread stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Slash edges of ham slices to prevent curling.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.

title: jake's fudge
directions: Line a
9 x 13-inch pan with foil.
Place peanut butter chips and chocolate chips each in a separate bowl.
Pour 1 can condensed milk into each bowl.
Microwave bowl with peanut butter chips on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes until mixture is smooth when stirred. Add butter. Pour mixture into pan and spread evenly.
Microwave bowl with chocolate chips for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir until smooth and pour over top of peanut butter layer.
Cool, cover and chill until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix all together and form into patties.
Makes about 7 (2-inch) patties.
Fry lightly in small amount of oil.
Turn heat down and cover patties with white sauce.
Simmer approximately 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes and paprika, if desired.

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and pat into a 9x13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: apple oatmeal muffins(low calorie - low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine wet and dry ingredients separately.
Fold together until blended.
Spoon into paper cup liners in a muffin pan and bake for 25 minutes.
Yields about 23 muffins, 2 ounces each.

title: icebox cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin and marshmallows in boiling water; stir well. Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add 1 cup pineapple juice to gelatin mixture.
(Add water to pineapple juice to make 1 cup, if necessary.)
Chill until partially set. Whip gelatin mixture until frothy.
Blend whipped cream, pineapple and angel food cake pieces into gelatin mixture.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan; chill.
Makes 12 or more servings.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Lightly grease a cookie sheet and set aside.
Mix sugar, syrup, water and salt in a skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Boil until clear.
Add peanuts; stir continuously while boiling until candy is brittle when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat, but continue stirring until it stops bubbling.
Add baking soda. Mixture will foam up.
Stir until well mixed and pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Let set until cool and break into small pieces.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk, then add oleo.
Place on low flame while oleo melts.
Turn up flame and boil for 5 minutes; stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add the chocolate chips, Hershey bar and Marshmallow Fluff.
Spread on jelly roll pan.
Cool; cut into 1-inch squares.

title: yogurt shake
directions: Place milk, yogurt and rum extract in blender; blend until smooth.
Serve immediately or refrigerate until ready to serve. To serve, stir, pour into glasses and sprinkle each serving with nutmeg.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite-size pieces (this will take about 2 months).
Add enough gravy to cover.
Cook over kerosene fire at 450° for 4 weeks.
This will serve 3800 people.
If more are expected, add the 2 rabbits, but do this only if necessary for most people don't like to find hare in their stew!

title: maryland cream of crab soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon cube in milk.
In 4-quart saucepan cook onion in butter until tender.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add half and half and bouillon gradually and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens enough to coat spoon. Add crabmeat; heat but do not boil.
Garnish with parsley flakes before serving.
Soup improves upon standing.
Never let boil! Add Old Bay for seasoning.
Sometimes a little Cheddar cheese and sherry are good.

title: extra moist chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour two 9-inch layer cake pans.
In a large bowl with mixer at low speed, blend all ingredients 30 seconds.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake pulls away from sides of pan.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove and frost with favorite frosting.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites and salt until thick. Gradually add sugar and beat until stiff.
Stir in pecans and chips.
Drop cookies on pan lined with foil.
Place in oven and turn off oven.
Leave in closed oven overnight.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: pasta with spring peas
directions: Combine pasta, peas, onions and pepper in salad bowl.
Mix milk, vinegar, mayonnaise, parsley and sweetener.
Pour dressing over first ingredients and toss; season.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chocolate layer dessert
directions: Pour milk into bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes.
Let stand
5 minutes.
Gently stir in 2 cups of the whipped topping and half of the cubes in a 3 1/2-quart serving bowl.
Drizzle with half the chocolate syrup.
Layer with half the chopped candy bars and half the pudding mixture.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: squash patties
directions: Slice squash and boil until tender. Drain and mash with fork. Add egg, flour and milk, mixing well. Salt and pepper to taste. Spoon mixture into frying pan with melted butter.
Fry until browned.

title: honey-mustard chicken
directions: Stir salad dressing, mustard and honey.
Brown chicken.
Brush with 1/2 dressing.
Pan roast 10 minutes, brush again with dressing and roast 10 minutes more.
Cooking time, 20 minutes.

title: oreo cake
directions: Crush 28 cookies and mix with melted butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip. Spread over crumb mixture.
Make vanilla and chocolate pudding separately, using 2 cups of milk for each.
Spread vanilla pudding over cheese and chocolate pudding on top.
Spoon rest of Cool Whip and sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: salad
directions: Grate cheese. Rinse beans in cold water and mix altogether.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onions, bell pepper, salt and pepper. Simmer 5 minutes.
Cover bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole with a layer of potatoes, one layer of beef, etc.
Pour half soup, alternate until complete.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes whole, with or without peel, or peel and cut into large chunks.
While potatoes boil, dice onions and, if desired, dice chives and/or parsley and add to onions.
Combine oil and vinegar; set aside.
Boil water, or, for better flavor, use 3/4 cup of water in which potatoes are boiled.
Dissolve mustard in water or potato liquid.
Drain potatoes and slice quickly (peel first, if necessary).
Salt and pepper potatoes, then add onion and vinegar mixtures.
Can be served hot or cold. Excellent for picnics or travel as mayonnaise is not used.

title: cherry salad
directions: Heat water to boiling.
Stir in cherry pie filling plus sugar. Bring back to boiling.
Remove and stir in cherry jello.
Set aside to cool.
Add Coca-Cola.
Put in mold and refrigerate overnight.
Very good!

title: marinated turkey
directions: In large stockpot, in chicken broth, boil all the spices to begin bouquet and let cool. Place cleaned turkey in brine, breast side down. Cover turkey with water and top with ice. Put lid on. Refrigerate. In winter, when garage temperature under 30°, I have done this outside and had no problems. Marinate in brine 12 to 15 hours. Remove turkey; wash and pat dry. Rub olive oil on turkey. Discard brine and spices. In roasting pan, breast side up, place turkey on rack. Put thermometer in breast. Cook 1 1/2 hours at 500° with a foil tent. Uncover. Reduce heat to 350°; cook another 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until thermometer reaches 185°. This is a very moist and delicious turkey! Serves 8. Can freeze.

title: krispie roll
directions: Mix all ingredients except cereal.
Cook for 10 minutes on low heat, stirring constantly.
Add cereal.
Cool.
Shape into two logs and roll in powdered sugar.
Refrigerate and slice.

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into serving dishes.
Chill and serve.

title: mother's sensational strawberry pie
directions: Arrange largest strawberries in bottom of a 9-inch baked pie crust.

title: banana salad
directions: Mix pudding in Cool Whip until dissolved.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Chill.

title: grilled rosemary chicken breasts
directions: Prepare charcoal for grilling.
Place chicken breasts in a wide shallow dish.
Sprinkle with garlic and rosemary; then drizzle with oil and vinegar.
Season lightly with black pepper. Turn breasts to coat and combine.
Let marinate, turning once or twice at room temperature, 15 to 30 minutes.
When coals are ready, arrange chicken on grill.
Add chicken; grill, turning once, until golden brown on outside and just cooked through, 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: party potatoes
directions: Combine
first
five
ingredients.
Place
in	3-quart buttered casserole dish.
Top this with cream of chicken soup, sour
cream and Cheddar cheese, mixed together.
Top this with crushed corn flakes and 1/4 cup melted butter, mixed together. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.	Cover when baking.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Mix together with fingers.
Roll into bite size balls and bake or freeze.
When frozen, package in freezer bags.
Bake on cookie sheet in 300° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes about walnut size balls.

title: steak a la king
directions: Place steak in ungreased, unheated iron skillet.
Slice lemon. Place on steak.
Cut onion into thin slices and pepper into thin rings.
Place on steak.
Cover all with ketchup.
Use 2 tablespoons water to rinse ketchup bottle.
Cover with tight fitting lid.
Cook in 300° oven 1 1/2 to 2 hours until fork-tender.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar, butter and vanilla together. Whip heavy cream until it becomes like egg whites. Mix into cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar, butter and vanilla. Pour into graham cracker crust. Shred chocolate bar on top of pie. Freeze for 2 hours.

title: lemon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients and beat for 10 minutes.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 65 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: congealed salmon salad
directions: Drain salmon, reserving liquid.
Add enough hot water to salmon liquid to measure 1 cup.
Bring liquid to a boil; pour over gelatin, stirring well.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Take salmon.
Add gelatin mixture, vegetables, salad dressing, lemon juice and salt.
Stir until blended well.
Arrange egg slices in bottom of a 4-cup mold.
Spoon salmon mixture over eggs and chill until firm.
Unmold on lettuce.
Yields 6 to 8 servings. Mayonnaise should not be substituted for salad dressing.
Instead of eggs, I use a slice of stuffed pimiento.

title: pumpkin spice muffins
directions: Mix ingredients. Spray muffin tins with Pam. Fill muffin tins halfway with batter. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Makes 24 muffins.

title: penny cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add tomato paste, onion, salt, Italian seasoning and pepper; blend well.
Separate rolls into 8 triangles.
Place in ungreased 9-inch pie pan, pressing pieces together to form crust.
Place meat in crust.
Top with cheese. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: meatballs and sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into balls and place into baking dish.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and oatmeal.
Chill dough. Form into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Press down with a cup.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375°.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix ingredients the day before serving.
Hollow out center of dark round bread.
Place in oven at 350° and bake about 15 to 20 minutes.
Fill center with dip and serve.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix. Layer all ingredients in a dish.

title: skillet barbecued chicken
directions: Set electric skillet to 360°.
Heat oil and brown chicken on all sides.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Cook onion until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Return chicken to skillet. Turn skillet to simmer and cook, covered, for 30 minutes to 1 hour or until chicken is tender.

title: dijon mustard marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients into bowl and whisk until incorporated.
Apply liberally to chicken, fish, meat and pork. Let stand 1 to 3 hours and cook as desired.

title: eden isle chicken
directions: Place dried beef in a large casserole dish.
Wrap a slice of bacon around each breast.
Mix sour cream, cream cheese and soup together.
Cover chicken with mixture.
Cook at 325° for 2 hours. Twenty minutes before done, remove aluminum foil to brown.
Serve over rice.

title: pauline's six week bran muffins
directions: Mix together the raisin bran, flour, sugar, baking soda and salt. Add the remaining ingredients and mix well. Fill muffin cups with batter. Bake at 350° for 20-30 minutes. Refrigerated batter may be kept in a sealed container for up to 6 weeks.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in an ovensafe dish.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes, then uncovered for 15 minutes.

title: corn custard
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° about 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: antipasto pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and rinse with cold water until completely cool.

title: fancy cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix in 9 x 13-inch pan.
When cool, mix the vanilla pudding with milk and cream cheese.
Spread over cake, then add drained pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip and crushed nuts.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour 1 cup boiling water over the All-Bran and set aside.

title: diabetic bran muffins
directions: Mix together; bake at 350° for 20 minutes in greased muffin pan.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil and sugar.
Combine dry ingredients in separate bowl.
Add zucchini, carrots and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add raisins and nuts.
Pour into
2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool in pans for 10 minutes before removing.

title: salmon with basil cream sauce
directions: Cut salmon in pieces.
Wash.
Pat dry.
Melt butter in skillet over medium-high heat.
Sear salmon 2 to 3 minutes on each side. Remove fish with slotted spatula and keep warm.
Reduce heat to low.
Add shallots and garlic to pan.
Saute while stirring.
Add basil, parsley, wine, cream, lemon juice, pepper and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, until mixture is reduced by about half. To serve, reheat fish slightly in sauce and serve sauce over fish.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix stuffing with melted oleo. Add 1/2 to first five ingredients, sprinkle 1/2 on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Break cake in small pieces and set aside.
Mix milk and sugar until dissolved.
Mix cream cheese with Cool Whip.
Combine the two mixtures.
Fold in cake pieces.
Put in 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Spread cherry pie filling over top.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: chocolate chip cake mix cookies
directions: Just mix all the ingredients in a bowl.
Drop them on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat in melted butter.
Cook about 1 hour.
Remove meat; add onions and green pepper.
Saute about 2 minutes.
Return meat with tomatoes and bouillon cube dissolved in 1/4 cup water.
Add soy sauce, sugar and salt.
Stir into meat mixture and cook until thick and tender.

title: diabetic pink salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and pineapple; bring to boil. Let cool. Add cottage cheese and topping. Chill 4 to 6 hours. Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy punch
directions: Pour chilled pineapple juice into punch bowl.
Add frozen sherbet and pour in chilled 7-Up.
Your punch will be the color of your sherbet.
This is a very easy punch and tastes good too!

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup of boiling water.
Add enough cold water to pineapple juice to make 1 cup.
Pour over dissolved jello.
Chill until it gets thick.
Stir in pineapple and oranges. Fold in Cool Whip.
Cool to congeal.

title: chicken rice
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add mixed vegetables to onions. Simmer.
Add rice and chicken; mix well.
Season with pepper.

title: oatmeal-raisin cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg.
Reduce mixer speed and mix in dry ingredients and flavoring.
Stir in raisins.
Drop the dough by tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets, spacing them about 2-inches apart. Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: In covered skillet, pour oil, place onions and salt and saute until brown.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons paprika and meat.
Mix well. Cover and simmer, over very low heat, for 1 hour.
Add 4 1/2 teaspoons paprika, water and potatoes to meat.
Cover; simmer, over low heat, for 45 to 60 minutes, until tender.
May add more water as needed for gravy.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grate zucchini and wring out excess moisture by twisting gratings in cheesecloth.
Beat together the oil, honey, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Combine the 2 mixtures.
Stir to blend.
Add nuts, raisins and zucchini.
Place in greased and floured loaf pan and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: jalapeno cheese spread
directions: *May add more if desired.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix meat and onions and cook together until done.
Drain. Pour into large baking dish.
Spread soup mixture on top of meat. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
A hearty meal, served with rolls and salad.
tags: cream of chicken and rice soup

title: hot spicy pepper steak
directions: Combine soy sauce, Worcestershire, ginger, cornstarch and picante sauce in small bowl and set aside.
Over high heat in large skillet or wok, heat 2 tablespoons of oil until hot, but not smoking.
Add meat and stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Heat remaining 2 tablespoons oil in skillet.
Add garlic, peppers, mushrooms and onions.
Stir-fry 3 minutes.
Return meat to skillet.
Stir in picante sauce mixture.
Add water.
Cook and stir about 1 minute or until sauce thickens.
Serve over hot rice.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter or oleo.
Add soup, milk, broccoli and cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
Mix with rice.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: family pie
directions: Mix together smoothly with complete faith in God.
Add two tablespoonfuls of wisdom and one teaspoonsful good nature for flavor. Then sprinkle generously with thoughtfulness.
This makes a wonderful family pie!

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix butter, flour and powdered sugar together.
Pat in 10 or 11-inch pan and bake 12 minutes in a 325° oven.
Meanwhile, beat eggs, lemon juice, rind, sugar and baking powder together.
Pour on the crust.
Bake 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pineapple creme
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve as a fruit salad on lettuce or as a dessert with a sprinkling of coconut.
Serves 6.

title: luscious peach pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and extract.
Beat until smooth.
Gently fold in whipped topping and peaches.
Pour into pie crust and chill until firm (about 3 hours).

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Place ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch pan one layer at a time in the order given.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fried onion rings
directions: Cut onions into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Separate slices into rings; set aside.
Combine in a large bowl the flour, salt, paprika and pepper.
Dip rings into evaporated milk, then coat with flour mixture.
Cook in hot oil until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent towel.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Add all ingredients into food processor and blend.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: spicy turkey-tortilla casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook turkey, onion, vinegar, oregano, paprika, salt, cumin, red pepper and garlic in skillet over medium heat until turkey is brown.
Spread half of the salsa in bottom of ungreased square baking dish (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Mix remaining salsa, sour cream and broth.
Layer half each of the tortilla strips, turkey mixture and sour cream mixture on salsa in baking dish.
Repeat.
Bake, uncovered, about 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serve it with chopped lettuce, tomato, black olives and red onion.

title: mario's smilin snacks(for children to make)
directions: With Mom's assistance, prepare instant pudding as directed on package for pudding in a small bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes, then spoon into four 5-ounce paper cups.
Make faces with M&M's, gumdrops, jelly beans, raisins, Baker's coconut, cinnamon candies, cereal, chocolate chips or anything you like.
Fun for the young cooks!

title: mom's white cake "lite"
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and oil.
Beat well with spoon.
Add milk alternately with 1 cup flour, baking powder and salt, using triple sieve.
Add 1 more cup flour; stir and beat with electric mixer. Spray and line 9 x 13-inch pan with parchment paper or waxed paper.
With spatula, fold into pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
Top with favorite topping.
Ideal for shortcakes.

title: okra and tomatoes(georgia gumbo)
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in bacon grease in skillet over medium heat until tender.
Add tomatoes, vinegar, water, salt and pepper; stir well.
Cover and cook over low heat, 5 to 10 minutes. Add sliced okra; cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: sweet potato surprise
directions: Cook potatoes until tender; drain.
Peel and slice lengthwise. Arrange in casserole.
Mix sugar, butter, cinnamon and vanilla; cook for 8 minutes or until butter is melted.
Add pineapple, coconut and pecans.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with marshmallows; bake until marshmallows are golden brown.
Serves eight.

title: teddy pops
directions: On a foil lined baking sheet, arrange 6 Teddies in a circle. Repeat to make a total of 5 circles for each pop.
Crush 2 candies and spoon in an even layer in the center of each circle.
Position the end of a stick near the center of each circle.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes or until candy melts and begins to bubble. Cool.
Peel pops from foil and repeat for rest of ingredients. Store in an airtight container.

title: martha's coconut cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt, milk and egg yolks in saucepan.
Cook until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in butter, vanilla and coconut.
Cool and pour into pastry shell.
Top with favorite topping (Cool Whip or meringue).
Garnish with toasted coconut.

title: mom's applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add beaten eggs and applesauce. Add flour, spices, salt, soda, raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: tabouleh
directions: Wash bulghur wheat and soak in water and set aside.
Pick parsley and mint leaves, no stems, chop very fine.
Chop scallion very fine.
Mix in bowl with tomatoes and all spices and seasonings.
Drain all the water from the wheat and add it (wheat) to the chopped vegetables.
Mix well and adjust seasonings to taste.

title: hamburger casserole *
directions: Brown meat in butter.
Add salt, pepper, tomato sauce, sugar and garlic, simmering, covered for 20 minutes.
Cook noodles until tender and drain under cold water.
Allow cream cheese to soften and mix with sour cream, adding onions.
Place ingredients in layers in casserole:
1/2 meat mixture, noodles, rest of the meat mixture, then cheese.
Spread topping with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix macaroni, red bell pepper, green bell pepper, onion and carrots; add white vinegar, sugar, salad dressing, salt and pepper.
